<interpreter id="EN42" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1248:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1248&start=00.00.01&end=00.00.20">
President , on the agenda I ... ask you to ask lady Ashton to come to the Chamber to tell us what she has done or will do about what 's happening ... with Christians throughout the world .
</s>
<s id="1248:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1248&start=00.00.20&end=00.00.25">
I 'd like her to come and report to us , so Parliament can have a detailed report on that .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1249" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="105" duration="short" durations="48.0" speed="medium" speedwm="131.2" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Order of business" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mauro Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="104" duration="short" durations="46.0" speed="medium" speedwm="135.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1249:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1249&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.15">
Yeah thank you President .
</s>
<s id="1249:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1249&start=00.00.17&end=00.00.55">
On behalf of my group and , I think , the whole of the Parliament , I want to stress how warm our relations were with the Brazilian government and people and our solidarity and sympathy with them because of the floods in the last few days , where ... hundreds of people lost their lives and we 'd like to express once again ou- our great sorrow and solidarity , but on ... this particular issue I would say , wish to , extremely keen to talk about this , because the whole issue has not yet been completely sorted out in the court .
</s>
<s id="1249:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1249&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.00">
We need to talk about it in the European Parliament , we need to have our voice heard on the international stage .
</s>
<s id="1249:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1249&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.01">
Thank you President .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1250" date="2011-01-17" length="medium" lengthw="485" duration="medium" durations="232.0" speed="slow" speedwm="125.4" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Statement by the President of the European Parliament on the situation in Tunisia" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Panzeri Pier Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="537" duration="medium" durations="230.0" speed="medium" speedwm="140.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1250:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.22">
Thank you Mr President , we share the concern about what 's going on in Tunisia and we express our condolences to those who have lost family and friends during the recent events .
</s>
<s id="1250:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.40">
The confused situation after the flight of President Ben Ali should , or I hope , lead to a situation that we all want to see : social and economic reform which will meet the concerns of the vast majority of the people and the broadening out of the democratic space in the country .
</s>
<s id="1250:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.00.40&end=00.00.46">
We need a civil society and a proper democratic pluralist ... political system .
</s>
<s id="1250:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.00.46&end=00.01.00">
Obviously , countries are all free to choose their own path and we just want these changes to happen and be genuine and effective and not just a bit of surface trickery .
</s>
<s id="1250:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.07">
But ... also there 's the question of what 's happening and Europe's role in all of this .
</s>
<s id="1250:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.01.07&end=00.01.20">
The Barcelona process beginning in the 1990s , should have had economic , political cooper- and even military cooperation , but not even the 2 main goals we set ourselves have worked .
</s>
<s id="1250:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.01.20&end=00.01.28">
The regional and infrastructural programmes were cut because the money never arrived from Europe .
</s>
<s id="1250:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.01.30&end=00.01.40">
The idea of a free trade area never worked and the most clear failure is the political area , which the Commissioner has admitted .
</s>
<s id="1250:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.01.41&end=00.02.10">
The 2008 initiative is just a piece of a f- ehm fa√ßade with no real content and various European governments clearly are uninterested in real cooperation and ehm want to continue to have links with ehm dubious regimes whose democratic record leaves a lot to be desired whereas the people live in misery and often take the dangerous route of flight and exile .
</s>
<s id="1250:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.02.11&end=00.02.21">
The economic and social crisis has led to the ... demonstrations in Tunisia which turned into a tidal wave which swept the government away .
</s>
<s id="1250:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.02.21&end=00.02.29">
The ... realpolitik of Europe can no longer work in a world where we also have Islamic fundamentalism .
</s>
<s id="1250:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.02.30&end=00.02.39">
We need to remove from ourselves this occasional colonialist view which we have with certain North African countries .
</s>
<s id="1250:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.02.39&end=00.02.48">
Let 's have a real , proper Barcelona process where we look with more credibility as far as these countries are concerned .
</s>
<s id="1250:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.02.48&end=00.03.04">
So I urgently ask the Commissioner to overhaul neighbourhood and partnership policy with tha- which we wo n't be able to conceal the fact that Commission and Council were happy about talking with advanced status for Tunisia .
</s>
<s id="1250:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.03.05&end=00.03.14">
And we have to und- work out precisely why they were willing to talk about that with the old , corrupt Tunisian government .
</s>
<s id="1250:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.03.14&end=00.03.28">
What we need to do is associate this Parliament with the process and rethink the whole idea of partnership with our Mediterranean counterparts , in the interest of those countries but in particular in the interest of Europe .
</s>
<s id="1250:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.03.28&end=00.03.35">
Many of the problems we have can only be sorted out through a productive relationship with Maghreb countries .
</s>
<s id="1250:18" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.03.36&end=00.03.46">
It 's a tricky road , but it 's the only one that we can go down : support economic and democratic reforms and simultaneously do everything we can to combat fundamentalism and terrorism .
</s>
<s id="1250:19" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.03.47&end=00.04.00">
We should be pleased that from this dramatic election in Tunisia we can learn something which will be useful for all of us , what we need to do ehm what we should be changing as far as Europe's action in the area is concerned .
</s>
<s id="1250:20" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1250&start=00.04.00&end=00.04.00">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1251" date="2011-01-17" length="medium" lengthw="747" duration="long" durations="422.0" speed="slow" speedwm="106.2" delivery="read" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Harmonised conditions for the marketing of construction products" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Tajani Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="European Commission" politgroup="NA">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="749" duration="long" durations="423.0" speed="slow" speedwm="106.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1251:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.27">
Thank you Mr President , honourable members of the European Parliament , let me begin ... by thanking you Mr President for coming and chairing a debate that 's so important for Europe's industrial policy and for the internal market .
</s>
<s id="1251:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.41">
I 'd also like to thank Mrs Stihler , the rapporteur , who has worked long and hard on this proposal and , thanks to her commitment , we have reached an agreement in second reading .
</s>
<s id="1251:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.00.43&end=00.00.51">
I 'd also like to thank all the shadow rapporteurs , the Chair of the internal market committee Mr Harbour .
</s>
<s id="1251:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.13">
The collective efforts of honourable members were crucial in achieving ehm crossroads and making process in what i- progress in what is an extremely technical ... issue and we in the Commission welcome the second-reading agreement between Parliament and Council ;
</s>
<s id="1251:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.01.14&end=00.01.17">
over and above the technical aspects , this is an extremely important issue .
</s>
<s id="1251:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.01.18&end=00.01.27">
Adoption of the construction products Directive is a huge step forward for the whole European construction sector .
</s>
<s id="1251:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.01.28&end=00.01.52">
Although these products represent 3 percent of European GDP and , in terms of employment , ac- activities ... linked to the sector in fact ... are generating 6.5 of Europe's GDP and account for about 7 percent of Europe's employment .
</s>
<s id="1251:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.01.52&end=00.02.02">
So we 're talking about a sector which probably takes up about 10 percent of Europe's economy , as Mrs Sthiler reminded us when she spoke .
</s>
<s id="1251:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.02.03&end=00.02.17">
The adoption of the construction products Directive is also a significant step forward when it comes to simplification and better legislation and helps the internal market in construction products .
</s>
<s id="1251:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.02.19&end=00.02.28">
It 's also the first opportunity to apply the pris- prisons of the Small Business Act .
</s>
<s id="1251:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.02.29&end=00.02.48">
It 's often the smallest companies that have suffered under European legislation , but now we are moving things forward and making it easier for them to fill in the various forms that are involved and all of this through legislative simplification .
</s>
<s id="1251:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.02.50&end=00.03.08">
And a lot of simplification has been brought in first of all as far as dangerous substances is concerned , the Commission is gonna draw up a report on this s- particular issue and it will brief the Parliament and , if necessary , come up with the requisite legislative proposals .
</s>
<s id="1251:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.03.08&end=00.03.22">
Second , the special treatment for micro-companies ... this is something ehm that 's always been regarded as crucially important and that was gonna be of course part of the Small Business Act .
</s>
<s id="1251:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.03.22&end=00.03.50">
And we want to make sure that we keep these simplified procedures which are going to be very useful for micro-companies and in fi- in various parts of the text , my final point is , that the need to cut red tape and tests is going to be important , not simply as far as the mark is concerned , but also the use of European technical evaluation .
</s>
<s id="1251:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.03.53&end=00.04.09">
But as the Commission declaration annexed to Council's ehm f- position at first reading is concerned , we need to make certain that the positions adopted really are the best ones to tackle the real needs of the situation .
</s>
<s id="1251:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.04.09&end=00.04.37">
We need to make certain that we do n't oblige companies , particularly the very small ones , to undergo excessive bureaucracy ehm ... or any unnecessary extra work and we 've made this clear in our conclusion ... and our views are being given to Parliament and Commission and we are of course going to revisit the Directive after it 's been enforced for 5 years .
</s>
<s id="1251:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.04.38&end=00.04.51">
Commission also wants ... to work closely with Parliament and the Council ... as far as the actual implementation of the regulation is concerned .
</s>
<s id="1251:18" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.04.51&end=00.05.02">
And I called upon my services and I 'd like to thank them for the tremendous work that they 've put in as they always do to draw up a road map on implementation .
</s>
<s id="1251:19" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.03&end=00.05.08">
The idea is that we forward this to the House as soon as possible .
</s>
<s id="1251:20" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.09&end=00.05.11">
There 's also the question of comitology , Mr President .
</s>
<s id="1251:21" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.11&end=00.05.25">
Parliament is a k- key partner for the Commission and I can promise that we continue ... we want to continue to work closely with Parliament in successive phases of the adoption of all of this .
</s>
<s id="1251:22" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.26&end=00.05.31">
I of course spent 14 years in this Chamber and is not been in vain .
</s>
<s id="1251:23" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.32&end=00.05.48">
And we also intend to submit a declaration on a derogation to the common agreement between the institutions on the deadline for le- for lodging ... objections to delegated acts .
</s>
<s id="1251:24" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.05.48&end=00.06.02">
The ... common agreement says that these objections have to be ... lodged within a 2-month period , which could be extended for a further 2 months .
</s>
<s id="1251:25" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.06.03&end=00.06.15">
Commission believes that unless ... there are ... exigent circumstances we really should n't be looking at any derogations at all .
</s>
<s id="1251:26" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.06.16&end=00.06.29">
And we stress , once again , that construction products and any derogations could not been regarded as a precedent for any other type of European legislation .
</s>
<s id="1251:27" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.06.29&end=00.06.44">
I 'd like to thank everybody who 's contributed to the debate , Mr President , and people whose willingness to look at this proposal for simplification and Parliament has highlighted the advantages that will flow from this new legislation .
</s>
<s id="1251:28" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.06.47&end=00.06.55">
Those both for those who produce and use construction products as well as national administrations .
</s>
<s id="1251:29" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.06.55&end=00.07.04">
Commission is , I can confirm , willing to meet everything , to implement everything incumbent upon it in the legislation .
</s>
<s id="1251:30" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1251&start=00.07.04&end=00.07.12">
And I 'd like to thank you once again President , and thank the honourable members of the Parliament for the commitment that they 've shown and all this in a cooperative spirit .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1252" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="171" duration="short" durations="92.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.5" delivery="read" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Harmonised conditions for the marketing of construction products" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Comi Lara" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="188" duration="short" durations="91.0" speed="slow" speedwm="124.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1252:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.00.12&end=00.00.13">
Thank you madam President .
</s>
<s id="1252:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.29">
I ... welcome the compromise reached on certain specific points which I think are crucially important if we want to effectively to achieve the goals ehm we want to reach through this legislation .
</s>
<s id="1252:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.00.30&end=00.00.40">
I 'm talking about the simplified procedure ... which will reduce administrative burdens and costs for companies , particularly SMEs .
</s>
<s id="1252:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.57">
It 's vital ... in ... a negative economic climate such as we have today to recognise the crucial role played by SMEs , who are one of the key-pillars on which our economy is supporting .
</s>
<s id="1252:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.11">
I 'm also interested in the question of other simplified aspects , ways of for example reducing time limits for products to be launched onto the market , as well as innovative products .
</s>
<s id="1252:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.25">
Simultaneously , we have to protect consumers and make sure that they can benefit more speedily from innovative product developments ... without of course having to give up the guarantees of security and safety which the market should provide .
</s>
<s id="1252:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.01.26&end=00.01.43">
I think that this agreement is a splendid compromise which will ... strike the right balance between producer and consumer requirements and thus guaranteeing the correct functioning of the market in a sector which is vitally important for the European economy .
</s>
<s id="1252:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1252&start=00.01.43&end=00.01.44">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1253" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="390" duration="medium" durations="254.0" speed="slow" speedwm="92.1" delivery="impromptu" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Harmonised conditions for the marketing of construction products" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Tajani Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="European Commission" politgroup="NA">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="360" duration="medium" durations="250.0" speed="slow" speedwm="86.4" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1253:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.08">
Thanks very much madam President ...
</s>
<s id="1253:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.00.12&end=00.01.01">
I can endorse the remarks of the committee's Chairman Mr Harbour when he stresses the importance and significance of the text we are discussing , which , thanks to the agreement , will undoubtedly be adopted in the House because this is ... legislation which will ... provide signals to the market and simultaneously will establish decent rules to allow SMEs to develop , particularly ... during this , I hope , final phase of the crisis where we should do all we can to allow SMEs to generate new jobs and develop .
</s>
<s id="1253:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.10">
That 's the whole ... goal of the European Commission , and obviously Parliament is deeply committed to that as well .
</s>
<s id="1253:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.10&end=00.01.16">
And thanks to the Small Business Act this is going to happen .
</s>
<s id="1253:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.17&end=00.01.35">
Simplification for SMEs reducing the red tape that they need to go through and also ri- liberalising the market and assisting market development ... as Mrs Gebhardt pointed out as well .
</s>
<s id="1253:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.39&end=00.01.44">
It 's also not neglecting the question of safety .
</s>
<s id="1253:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.45&end=00.01.54">
Safety is hugely important both for the people who work in the construction sector and for , of course , consumers .
</s>
<s id="1253:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.01.54&end=00.02.00">
And I do believe that this text is going in the right direction there .
</s>
<s id="1253:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.02.01&end=00.02.15">
It is however , as I said before , the intention of the Commission not to stop when we 've adopted the ... legislation agreed upon by Parliament and Council .
</s>
<s id="1253:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.02.15&end=00.02.35">
We intend to continue during the next few years , and I repeat this promise and something President the Chairman Mr Harbour mentioned as well , the desire to go forward and have a road map on implementation , which I will send to Parliament as soon as it becomes available .
</s>
<s id="1253:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.02.35&end=00.02.51">
Many honourable members , during the discussion , madam President , spoke about harmonisation ... in the construction sector ... in particularly in particular as far as safety is concerned .
</s>
<s id="1253:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.02.51&end=00.03.13">
I am fully aware of the problem ... and ehm I 'm ... pleased that CEN has drawn up the Eurocodes , harmonised standards which deal with safety in the construction sector .
</s>
<s id="1253:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.03.13&end=00.03.29">
The Commission , as honourable members will be aware , is presently drawing up a s- communication on standardisation , which will be submitted in the next few weeks to Parliament and Council .
</s>
<s id="1253:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.03.30&end=00.03.41">
So , madam President , honourable members of the European Parliament ... today and tomorrow we are going to be making a significant step forward .
</s>
<s id="1253:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.03.45&end=00.03.59">
I 'd like to thank the rapporteur for her patience in grappling with this rather technical issue , but it does show the political commitment that we have here .
</s>
<s id="1253:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.04.00&end=00.04.18">
It is technical but it 's not just technical : behind the technical aspects there is a significant economic choice plumping for SMEs , because they are the ones who 'll be generating new jobs in Europe in the next few months and years and also for all of the citizens of the Union as well .
</s>
<s id="1253:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1253&start=00.04.18&end=00.04.20">
Thanks very much madam President .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1254" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="144" duration="short" durations="69.0" speed="slow" speedwm="125.2" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Consequences in the European Union of the dioxin animal feed incident" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="De Castro Paolo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="162" duration="short" durations="72.0" speed="medium" speedwm="135.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1254:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.20">
Madam President , Mr Commissioner , colleagues , let me thank Commissioner Dalli for having come this evening to talk about this matter which is of great concern to European citizens .
</s>
<s id="1254:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.26">
The agriculture committee , which I have the honour of chairing , will be looking into this next week .
</s>
<s id="1254:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.26&end=00.00.28">
It 's a very serious i- incident .
</s>
<s id="1254:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.41">
Europe is greatly involved in terms of food safety , we need to work harder as far as inspections are concerned to avoid other cases breaking out .
</s>
<s id="1254:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.58">
We adopted an own-initiative report recently on agricultural product safety and we 've also adopted the regulation on information to consumers on foodstuffs , making it lab- ma- mandatory that the label of a foodstuff includes where it comes from .
</s>
<s id="1254:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.12">
But on the 8th of December in the Council ... the issue was removed from the agenda and we want to bring it back on because it 's something that 's very important for European consumers' interest .
</s>
<s id="1254:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1254&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.18">
We are on the consumers' side and we 've demonstrated that and let's hope that the Council and the Commission do something similar .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1255" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="279" duration="medium" durations="122.0" speed="medium" speedwm="137.2" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Consequences in the European Union of the dioxin animal feed incident" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Ronzulli Licia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="265" duration="medium" durations="122.0" speed="medium" speedwm="130.3" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN43" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1255:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.21">
Thank you madam President , I wanted to be one of the signatories of this question because I think it 's crucial in the light of the incident that we have a debate on food safety in general .
</s>
<s id="1255:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.28">
Millions of European citizens consume these products every day and how safe are they ?
</s>
<s id="1255:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.33">
Are we sure that the stuff on our tables is safe ?
</s>
<s id="1255:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.33&end=00.00.38">
The quality of raw material is crucial to make sure that the final product is safe .
</s>
<s id="1255:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.48">
Constant inspection , from farm to fork , is vital if we are going to avoid contamination of food products and we can i- identify and eliminate potential risks .
</s>
<s id="1255:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.00.48&end=00.01.00">
This incident in Germany shows how important it is that all products , including processed products , should have an indication of origin on their label , as Mr De Castro's already mentioned .
</s>
<s id="1255:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.15">
We need to make sure that consumer's rights to know the origin of products that they 're purchasing is guaranteed and that the safety of our products can be guaranteed only through shared responsibility among all operators .
</s>
<s id="1255:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.01.15&end=00.01.34">
It 's quite true that European legislation does have inspections built into it so that the food on our tables is f- fit for consumption and that consumer risk is kept to a minimum , but our goal has to be now to contribute every day to improving the quality of this food .
</s>
<s id="1255:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.01.34&end=00.01.55">
I am proud to stress that the Italian Parliament tomorrow will adopt a rule which will extend the oblig- obligatory origin mark to all foodstuff produced in Italy and we 'll know now that where our pork ... meat , UHT milk , f- ehm fruit and vegetables we 'll know their origins .
</s>
<s id="1255:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.01.55&end=00.02.09">
So I do hope that Europe will be inspired by this legislation and I will always be working to make sure that the the utmost levels of transparency and information provided to consumers to provide genuine , healthy food for our citizens .
</s>
<s id="1255:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1255&start=00.02.09&end=00.02.10">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1256" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="288" duration="medium" durations="129.0" speed="medium" speedwm="134.0" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Angelilli Roberta" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="Vice President of the European Parliament" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="221" duration="medium" durations="128.0" speed="slow" speedwm="103.6" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1256:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.07">
Thank you , President .
</s>
<s id="1256:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.18">
Ehm many of my colleagues ehm , like me , over the years have become very much aware of the problem of abandoned children , orphans , street children .
</s>
<s id="1256:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.18&end=00.00.23">
Among the associations that got in touch with me ehm the Friends of Adoption .
</s>
<s id="1256:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.29">
These children are abandoned , there 's enough for lot of them , ehm not just in the third world , in Europe too .
</s>
<s id="1256:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.30&end=00.00.51">
Ehm they become invisible and away and they tend to wind up in the vicious circle of poverty and social exclusion or , even worse , they are exploited by organised crime for ehm informal economy , for ehm illegal adoption , for prostitution , ehm or for organ trafficking .
</s>
<s id="1256:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.00.51&end=00.00.59">
Often , they have to spend their childhood among ehm orphanages ehm social assistance , social workers .
</s>
<s id="1256:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.03">
Ehm we want to give them the right to be adopted , to have a family .
</s>
<s id="1256:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.09">
A child ehm should not stay in an institution any longer than necessary .
</s>
<s id="1256:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.26">
Ehm it 's in the ehm the higher interest of that child and therefore ... eligibility for adoption must be granted , of course , we must be very careful ehm that the competent authorities and the Member States must be very careful and ehm keeping tabs on this .
</s>
<s id="1256:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.26&end=00.01.35">
But , we must ehm honour the right of children to be ehm adopted nationally first and foremost , domestically , but then internationally within the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1256:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.35&end=00.01.57">
I know that the Commission is aware of the problem , although it is of course very much a national competence ehm but I think it would be a very good idea to have some kind of ehm coordination between the Commission and the Member States so that they can come up with strategies that would give us the best possible ehm transparency .
</s>
<s id="1256:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.01.58&end=00.02.15">
Ehm make adoption legal and easy but also between the Member States have as much ehm cooperation as possible in guaranteeing the right to adoption and to prevent children from being left to their own devices , or , as I said earlier , abandoned in an institution .
</s>
<s id="1256:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1256&start=00.02.15&end=00.02.15">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1257" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="352" duration="medium" durations="146.0" speed="medium" speedwm="144.7" delivery="mixed" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Iacolino Salvatore" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="250" duration="medium" durations="145.0" speed="slow" speedwm="103.4" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN04" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1257:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.23">
Thank you President , Commissioner , there 's no doubt that the subject of international adoption is ehm a very important subject , and I think Mrs Angelilli did well to put this oral question before Parliament at this part-session .
</s>
<s id="1257:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.25">
We need more streamlined procedures .
</s>
<s id="1257:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.00.26&end=00.00.49">
And ... w- we we need to , ehm at the moments when we see the people hav- having to spend 30,000 euros on starting adoption procedures and what we need to do is to en- ensure that we ehm m- meet the needs of ehm of people to become parents while meeting the needs also of abandoned children or children who are ehm who have become invisible .
</s>
<s id="1257:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.00.50&end=00.01.11">
I 'm referring here ehm to to these flows of ehm illegal migrants a lot of the children of ehm immigrant families ehm are put into ehm detention cent- centres in the host country and ehm they ehm o- often end up being trafficked or become ehm forc- ehm force forced workers .
</s>
<s id="1257:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.28">
All we need to do is ensure that ehm that we promote the ehm it- Italian family and the Italian family ehm is something which we should be ehm upholding and we m- and we must help str- ehm strengthen the fam- family by promoting international and intercountry adoptions .
</s>
<s id="1257:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.01.28&end=00.01.35">
We need as I said streamlined procedures and proper monitoring of what happenings in of what 's happening in the various Member States .
</s>
<s id="1257:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.01.35&end=00.01.42">
When it comes to adoption we need to fight against trafficking in human beings and the Parliament had dealt with these issues specifically recently .
</s>
<s id="1257:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.01.42&end=00.01.47">
We need to fight very hard against illegal adoptions , we need to create transparency .
</s>
<s id="1257:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.01.47&end=00.02.10">
And ehm if we want to give a ehm central role to the family , once again , we often talk about sub- strengthening ehm the family union that we have to ensure that associations ehm non-profit-making associations who often promote these i- intercountry adoptions are able to meet very high standards and en- ensure proper guarantees to these procedures .
</s>
<s id="1257:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.02.10&end=00.02.32">
So if there is a suggestion , Commission : why should n't we , for example , come up with some sort of European accreditation system for these ehm international adoption associations and this to ensure that these associations ehm work in the full light of the day and ehm th- th- th- they provide a high level of guarantees and they insure ehm the complete reflection of the rights of the children ?
</s>
<s id="1257:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1257&start=00.02.32&end=00.02.33">
Thank you very much .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1258" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="150" duration="short" durations="56.0" speed="high" speedwm="160.7" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Alfano Sonia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="150" duration="short" durations="57.0" speed="medium" speedwm="157.9" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN119" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1258:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1258&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.19">
President , for some years now in Italy various ehm families adopting Romanian children have undergone the consequences of ehm blocking of international adoption .
</s>
<s id="1258:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1258&start=00.00.20&end=00.00.28">
Now there is a Hague ehm reference we worked which is ehm uniform throughout the European countries and therefore Romania needs to make an effort to to catch up .
</s>
<s id="1258:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1258&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.43">
If Romania feels that the blocking of international adoption helps to protect children ... against the risk of illegal trafficking of the children then it should tackle this problem together with the ehm help of the European Union and ehm implement necessary controls .
</s>
<s id="1258:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1258&start=00.00.43&end=00.00.50">
However , a commitment is to be made in order to help families ehm welcome children that deserve a second opportunity for a happy childhood .
</s>
<s id="1258:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1258&start=00.00.51&end=00.01.06">
I would ask confirmation in what manner it intends ehm to help a commitment on the Eu- Romania cancel its morato- moratorium and I would also like to ask the Commission what it feels about setting up a European agency for adoption .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1259" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="219" duration="short" durations="108.0" speed="slow" speedwm="121.7" delivery="mixed" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Baldassarre Raffaele" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="221" duration="short" durations="109.0" speed="slow" speedwm="121.7" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN130" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1259:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.21">
Thank you very much President , Commissioner , colleagues , today , we are discussing something that is ehm a ehm a terrible contradiction .
</s>
<s id="1259:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.22">
We are a ...
</s>
<s id="1259:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.31">
Union who wants to have ehm full ehm freedom of movement for our citizens and yet in some areas this is restricted .
</s>
<s id="1259:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.32&end=00.00.43">
Now ... we have to ... ehm recognise that some people think it 's impossible for other parties to come in and provide the assistance that is so clearly needed .
</s>
<s id="1259:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.43&end=00.00.51">
It 's a paradox which turns into a tragedy for thousands of children and families within the EU .
</s>
<s id="1259:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.00.52&end=00.01.00">
Many international conventions have sort to deal with the problem of adoption but of any dealt with it in a partial way .
</s>
<s id="1259:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.14">
We have to look at the specific nature of the conventions ehm what they claim to cover and we also must recognise the intergovernmental nature of structures involved in decision-making .
</s>
<s id="1259:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.15&end=00.01.24">
Now looking at the Charter of Fundamental Rights ... that 's a legalistic approach , of course the political view might be different .
</s>
<s id="1259:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.24&end=00.01.31">
We have to have proper and full support of ehm children's well-being that should be one of the pillars of the Union .
</s>
<s id="1259:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.31&end=00.01.43">
That should underpin this debate ... we hope to have a broader debate on that basis and I 'm sure ehm it will be taken to heart by this Parliament .
</s>
<s id="1259:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.44&end=00.01.54">
Something we attach much importance to and ehm we need to take a very zealous approach as has been ehm pointed out ehm .
</s>
<s id="1259:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1259&start=00.01.55&end=00.01.59">
You know all adults were children once and let 's not forget that please .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1260" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="205" duration="short" durations="104.0" speed="slow" speedwm="118.3" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Scurria Marco" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="220" duration="short" durations="103.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN130" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1260:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.00.12&end=00.00.34">
Thank you very much President , well this evening we are looking at this ehm d- debate and ehm it 's of course it represents ehm input by very many associations throughout the EU who 've turned to us to ask us to take up this very sensitive issue ... that we have couched in the form of an oral ehm question for an oral answer .
</s>
<s id="1260:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.00.35&end=00.00.40">
It 's a very straightforward ehm problem or it certainly seems to be .
</s>
<s id="1260:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.00.40&end=00.00.48">
There are so very many children in institutions in the EU and there are so many families who wish to adopt children .
</s>
<s id="1260:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.00.49&end=00.00.56">
But unfortunately , the 2 do n't get matched up : the children stay in institutions and the families remain unable to adopt .
</s>
<s id="1260:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.04">
So ... that certainly has focused our attention on the problem .
</s>
<s id="1260:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.24">
When children remain too many years in ehm institutions , in ehm care institutions , they are ... prey to ehm people who 're seeking to involve them in prostitution and ehm ... criminal activities .
</s>
<s id="1260:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.01.25&end=00.01.46">
So , I 'd like to know what steps the Commission intends to take , surely there should be more cooperation between the Member States in the scenario of international adoption and of course there has to be ehm very ehm close attention paid to how the adopted children fare after the adoption .
</s>
<s id="1260:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1260&start=00.01.47&end=00.01.56">
These children are going to grow up and ehm become adults and they ehm have ehm just as much right ehm to care as others .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1261" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="289" duration="short" durations="114.0" speed="medium" speedwm="152.1" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mazzoni Erminia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="281" duration="short" durations="117.0" speed="medium" speedwm="144.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN121" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1261:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.30">
Thank you , I 've ... signed this because of my colleague Angelilli , because I believe that ehm straight after Lisbon , the European Union can not fail to set the protection of minors and adoption are quite simply a sign , an indication of a social problem .
</s>
<s id="1261:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.00.30&end=00.00.33">
It is our duty to take on board and setting limits .
</s>
<s id="1261:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.00.33&end=00.00.41">
Minors in the best ehm cases become the object of a trade which is ehm decidedly ehm lacking dignity for any of us .
</s>
<s id="1261:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.45">
But they 're frequently also the victims of violence and exploitation .
</s>
<s id="1261:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.00.45&end=00.01.07">
Quite apart f- from the phantoms are those ehm that are born into abandonment and are not taken into the system , there 's an uncertain number of children that could be adopted ... and there is a number of ehm couples who are wanting to adopt , but they never come together due to ehm excessive with- re- red tape .
</s>
<s id="1261:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.01.08&end=00.01.23">
UNICEF has ehm published a study indicating alarming data of many European countries and as ehm President of the relevant committee , I 've frequently afford when there has been a conflict of legislation between countries of the Union that lead to negative consequences for minors .
</s>
<s id="1261:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.01.24&end=00.01.49">
The complex procedures that exist under many legislations are not always in the interests of the minors and the very lengthy time ehm conflicts with the need to adopt the child within the first year of life in order to avoid a trauma and in order to avoid a lot of time being spent in an orphanage , and because once a child ehm exceeds a certain level then they 're not so desirable to the market unfortunately .
</s>
<s id="1261:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.01.49&end=00.02.07">
In the light of this , I feel it 's necessary ehm to undertake coordination at a European level of national legislation which will make it possible to simplify the ehm adoption procedures in Europe and will ensure the respect of the fundamental principles on the part of these countries outside Europe .
</s>
<s id="1261:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1261&start=00.02.07&end=00.02.08">
Thank you the Chair .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1262" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="175" duration="short" durations="94.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.7" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="International adoption in the European Union" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Pirillo Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="150" duration="short" durations="92.0" speed="slow" speedwm="97.8" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN126" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1262:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.12">
Thank you President , colleagues , Mrs Angelilli , madam Commissioner .
</s>
<s id="1262:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.26">
The protection and the care of ehm child welfare ... when the Lisbon Treaty came into force has become one of the basic rights ehm that Europe protects .
</s>
<s id="1262:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.37">
In spite on this , in Europe there are still too many incidents in which minors are abandoned ... are minors that finish up in orphanages .
</s>
<s id="1262:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.45">
This is a dramatic situation and which ehm is intolerable ehm for our democracies .
</s>
<s id="1262:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.54">
So , everything needs to be done in order to make sure that the situation v- not reach unmanageable proportions .
</s>
<s id="1262:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.04">
Implementing a strategy in order to raise awareness and in order ... also to make it easier to adopt minors at an international level .
</s>
<s id="1262:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.22">
In order to do this ... a careful picture of the situation is necessary in all Member countries , with constant monitoring to be done perhaps by setting up ehm a permanent , a centre for child's rights .
</s>
<s id="1262:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.01.23&end=00.01.40">
It is also necessary to have a care picture of the measures that have been taken by the European Union and those ... that could be taken in order to protect minors to the maximum , those minors that are up ehm for adoption by European citizens .
</s>
<s id="1262:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1262&start=00.01.40&end=00.01.41">
Thank you the Chair .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1263" date="2011-01-17" length="short" lengthw="136" duration="short" durations="66.0" speed="slow" speedwm="123.6" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="One minute speeches" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Alfano Sonia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="171" duration="short" durations="65.0" speed="medium" speedwm="157.8" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN130" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1263:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.09">
Thank you sir .
</s>
<s id="1263:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.22">
On the 13th and 14th of ehm January , there was ehm a referendum where ehm workers were ehm invited to ehm vote for relaunch of their Turin plant .
</s>
<s id="1263:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.36">
Now , we 're talking about fundamental labour rights being respected and ehm there was in fact an an 8-hour ehm strike affecting one of the assembly lines .
</s>
<s id="1263:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.37&end=00.00.47">
Now , if there was a " no " to the agreement , the count- the company said it was going to move out of Italy and have all of its operations carried out elsewhere .
</s>
<s id="1263:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.48&end=00.00.55">
It seems to me that ehm these rights should be supported by the government and we 're talking about a democratic tradition .
</s>
<s id="1263:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1263&start=00.00.56&end=00.01.15">
Now ... ehm a number of ehm unions were ehm derecognised ehm from ehm standing in representation of the workers and it seems to me that this is turning the clock back on ehm union rights ehm many decades if it 's allowed to go on .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1264" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="163" duration="short" durations="75.0" speed="medium" speedwm="130.4" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Review of the Belgian Presidency of the Council" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Baldassarre Raffaele" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="143" duration="short" durations="74.0" speed="slow" speedwm="115.9" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1264:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.21">
Ehm Mr President , ehm prime minister , ehm I have to say that I 'm satisfied with a Presidency which ehm managed to manage the European ehm diary in a pragmatic and effective way , in difficult times .
</s>
<s id="1264:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.40">
Ehm the approval at first reading of the di- le- payments Directive in the public administration , which is fundamental ehm for the future of companies , going as far as the super- financial supervision package , the Belgian Presidency has always been specific and dynamic .
</s>
<s id="1264:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.50">
I could go on with the list , but I prefer to draw some conclusions about what is to be learnt ehm from ehm a Presidency that has done such a good job .
</s>
<s id="1264:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.00.52&end=00.00.54">
First of all , you need a realistic work programme ;
</s>
<s id="1264:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.00.54&end=00.01.00">
you need to be able to negotiate dynamically ehm pointing toward a compromise ;
</s>
<s id="1264:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.15">
and , lastly , you need to involve the European institutions , starting with Parliament , and you need an approach ehm to the questions which is un- ehm which is freed from d- ehm links to national interest .
</s>
<s id="1264:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.01.15&end=00.01.19">
I hope that your Presidency will be an example to your successors .
</s>
<s id="1264:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1264&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.22">
For the moment on this Presidency my most sincere congratulations .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1265" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="159" duration="short" durations="70.0" speed="medium" speedwm="136.3" delivery="mixed" topic="Politics" topicspec="Review of the Belgian Presidency of the Council" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rossi Oreste" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="160" duration="short" durations="69.0" speed="medium" speedwm="139.1" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN75" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1265:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.25">
Thank you President , ehm you ehm had some important quotations in your speech , but unfortunately you , as a person , will be remembered mainly as prime minister of a Belgium ehm which , ehm 219 days after the elections , still did n't have a government .
</s>
<s id="1265:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.00.25&end=00.00.50">
I used to have a bad opinion - now I have changed it - of you , because , ehm when you came into office , I asked you , as the ehm President-in-Office for the next 6 months , what you were going to do about the very serious attacks on the Catholic Church in your country , things which subsequently the judges themselves ehm opposed and you did n't answer , which I did n't like .
</s>
<s id="1265:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.00.50&end=00.01.03">
But I think a Presidency has to be the Presidency for all , if it 's asked a question , it has to find some way of replying and making a brave choice , saying he 's in favour , saying he 's against , saying what he thinks .
</s>
<s id="1265:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.05">
But you did n't do any of that .
</s>
<s id="1265:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.10">
Today , I can say that your Presidency has been ehm a job well done .
</s>
<s id="1265:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1265&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.17">
And if you ehm ha- had been a bit more open with us right from the start , it would have been ehm better .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1266" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="181" duration="short" durations="93.0" speed="slow" speedwm="116.8" delivery="read" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Antoniozzi Alfredo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="175" duration="short" durations="89.0" speed="slow" speedwm="118.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN77" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1266:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.17">
I ca n't hear much , Mr President , ehm but on the Stihler report ... the importance of the building industry in Europe is obvious .
</s>
<s id="1266:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.26">
We had to face up to the problems ehm that ehm are faced by 12 million citizens who are directly employed in the industry .
</s>
<s id="1266:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.39">
Mrs Stihler's report is a useful instrument for knocking down the national administrative and technical barriers which prevent the marketing of construction products within the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1266:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.47">
It allows us to continue building an internal market in this sector .
</s>
<s id="1266:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.00.48&end=00.01.01">
I like the reference to SMEs in the building industry and the particular attention paid to the need to recycle construction products , this is crucial in fighting climate change .
</s>
<s id="1266:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.10">
But I 'd like to take this opportunity to point out that there are health and safety problems for building workers .
</s>
<s id="1266:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.17">
The guidelines that the rapporteur has included are useful , but not sufficient .
</s>
<s id="1266:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.01.18&end=00.01.28">
Our duty is to develop these things further in the immediate future , to make sure that building workers enjoy a high level of protection .
</s>
<s id="1266:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1266&start=00.01.30&end=00.01.39">
The ehm tragedy of ehm death at work is something that affects the whole of Europe and I hope that we can do something about it in this connection .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1267" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="144" duration="short" durations="67.0" speed="slow" speedwm="129.0" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mastella Clemente" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="160" duration="short" durations="67.0" speed="medium" speedwm="143.3" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1267:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.13">
President , the European Union is the first donor of humanitarian aid in the world , the biggest one .
</s>
<s id="1267:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.18">
Its contribution represents more than 40 percent of international humanitarian aid .
</s>
<s id="1267:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.30">
Through its humanitarian policy , the European Union demonstrates in specific terms its commitment to the peoples of third countries who need help because they are in extremely vulnerable positions .
</s>
<s id="1267:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.42">
The humanitarian consensus , signed on the 18th of December by the Council , the Commission and the European Parliament , represents a considerable step forward in this connection .
</s>
<s id="1267:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.44&end=00.00.48">
The commitments apply both to the Member States and to the European Commission .
</s>
<s id="1267:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.48&end=00.00.55">
In the last year , there 's been a growing involvement of humanitarian actors in the re- response to humanitarian crises .
</s>
<s id="1267:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.08">
The fundamental political and military and humanitarian actors are who have the same aims are ehm learning to know each other better and respecting their respective mandates .
</s>
<s id="1267:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1267&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.16">
Of course , protection civil protection measures taken have to be in line with this consensus reached within the European Union .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1268" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="168" duration="short" durations="84.0" speed="slow" speedwm="120.0" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Antinoro Antonello" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="166" duration="short" durations="82.0" speed="slow" speedwm="121.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1268:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.09">
Thank you President .
</s>
<s id="1268:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.24">
The report ehm passed ehm today by Mrs Striffler - to whom whom I congratulate - is something that will make humanitarian aid more effective and more efficient .
</s>
<s id="1268:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.40">
So the European Union now calls on the Union to collaborate more intensely in order to achieve a consensus , a collective response to humanitarian crises , in particular , fully to defend the res- respect for international humanitarian law .
</s>
<s id="1268:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.57">
We need to make sure that humanitarian actors can reach the needy populations ehm better , and since there are more of these recently , we need through the Commission or through bilateral agre- agreements to do something more than has been done so far .
</s>
<s id="1268:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.11">
The needs then are very great , the distribution of aid meanwhile is getting more and more difficult as well as dangerous and risky ehm in an ever more complex international context .
</s>
<s id="1268:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.22">
So this is an agreement of European common sense which sets that u- Union aid is based always on humanitarian principles , neutrality among others .
</s>
<s id="1268:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1268&start=00.01.22&end=00.01.31">
It needs to be provided quickly and efficiently to the victims ... on the basis of the the needs that have been identified .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1269" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="163" duration="short" durations="76.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.7" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Antoniozzi Alfredo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="160" duration="short" durations="76.0" speed="slow" speedwm="126.3" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1269:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.25">
The exponential increase of natural disasters , both in their number and in their seriousness , together with the multiplication of complex crises ... faces us with a more serious crisis of infringement of international human rights law .
</s>
<s id="1269:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.26&end=00.00.37">
Recent disasters in Haiti and Pakistan show once again the need to strengthen the tools available to the European Union , tools which it needs in order to deal with ehm natural disasters .
</s>
<s id="1269:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.40">
I agree with the general approach in the report .
</s>
<s id="1269:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.40&end=00.00.48">
As to specifics , there is a statement that the European Union should promote humanitarian principles ehm tirelessly .
</s>
<s id="1269:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.49&end=00.00.55">
External action of the European Union is ehm reflected in the Treaty of Lisbon ;
</s>
<s id="1269:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.00.56&end=00.01.02">
its action needs to reflect its ehm strengthen its profile as the major international aid donor .
</s>
<s id="1269:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.12">
I agree with Mrs Striffler that it needs to be an imperative to strengthen this consensus ... and so strengthen our action .
</s>
<s id="1269:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1269&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.26">
Ehm we need also to share the burdens out better at international level , at the same time there are regional responsibilities , there are countries that can contribute ehm substantially to humanitarian aid in that connection .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1270" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="143" duration="short" durations="67.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.1" delivery="read" topic="Agriculture and Fisheries" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mastella Clemente" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="141" duration="short" durations="66.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1270:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.16">
President , food security ehm represents a fundamental right ehm of humanity , and it needs to be specifically ehm realised .
</s>
<s id="1270:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.16&end=00.00.23">
It 's only when everybody , at all times , has ehm physical , social and economic access to sufficient nutrition that that right will be exercised .
</s>
<s id="1270:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.29">
The new common agricultural policy of the European Union will have to take this need into account .
</s>
<s id="1270:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.44">
So it will have to give a clear and unequivocal response to the challenge fa- represented by food security coming from , for example , climate change , the economic crisis and the maintenance of the territorial balance within the Union .
</s>
<s id="1270:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.45&end=00.00.55">
We need to encourage not just the competitiveness of our products , but also traditional agriculture , biological agriculture and local distribution networks .
</s>
<s id="1270:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.01">
This is a model that has always given , and always will give , a valid contribution to food security .
</s>
<s id="1270:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1270&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.13">
Often , they represent the most efficient way of using the land in different regions through methods that have been specifically developed in these specific regions over long periods .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1271" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="102" duration="short" durations="61.0" speed="slow" speedwm="100.3" delivery="read" topic="Agriculture and Fisheries" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Pirillo Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="long" lengthw="92" duration="short" durations="60.0" speed="slow" speedwm="92.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1271:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1271&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.08">
Thank you President .
</s>
<s id="1271:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1271&start=00.00.12&end=00.00.22">
Ehm food security , ehm reliable provision of food is a major challenge , not just in Europe but in the whole world .
</s>
<s id="1271:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1271&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.31">
I 'm very happy with the content of this report , above all , because it recognises food security as a fundamental right of humanity .
</s>
<s id="1271:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1271&start=00.00.32&end=00.00.48">
The objective of food security can be achieved will be achieved only if we deal with 2 fundamental questions - the volatility of markets and prices ehm and the reliability of supply .
</s>
<s id="1271:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1271&start=00.00.50&end=00.01.07">
Europe needs to take common , effective measures to ensure security of supply of food to avoid the considerable asymmetries that still exist in terms of safety standards ehm for EU products and products coming from outside .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1272" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="159" duration="short" durations="80.0" speed="slow" speedwm="119.2" delivery="read" topic="Agriculture and Fisheries" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Uggias Giommaria" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="154" duration="short" durations="78.0" speed="slow" speedwm="118.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1272:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1272&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.27">
Thank you President , in recent weeks , various parliamentary committees have been looking at the common agricultural policy and they 've been looking specifically it- at its reform , ehm that is to come after 2013 .
</s>
<s id="1272:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1272&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.52">
Among the fundamentals of agriculture it 's always been clear that food security is an important one and that needs to be assessed in the light of the s- the provision ehm in front of us this morning , which talks about food security as a fundamental right and therefore ehm something to be protected in all possible ways .
</s>
<s id="1272:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1272&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.19">
But that same attention needs to apply both at moments of emergency , as , for example , what the dioxin scandal ehm that we are living through these days , dioxin discovered on on ehm farms , but also under ordinary conditions when you look at the entire production chain , the quality of life of ... farmers and the quality of the environment and the conditions under which food is marketed .
</s>
<s id="1272:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1272&start=00.01.20&end=00.01.29">
So , this ... is a provision that Parliament has approved as part of a series of agricultural measures and in that sense I 'm happy with it .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1273" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="133" duration="short" durations="80.0" speed="slow" speedwm="99.8" delivery="read" topic="Agriculture and Fisheries" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Tatarella Salvatore" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="119" duration="short" durations="78.0" speed="slow" speedwm="91.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1273:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1273&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.26">
Thank you President , I voted ehm in a convinced way in favour of this important report and I would now like , in particular , to stress point 35 ehm of the Environment committee's opinion .
</s>
<s id="1273:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1273&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.58">
This talks about the importance of the European agency for food ehm security , food safety rather , in assessing all the risks attached to the food ehm chain with a view to protecting citizens' health , it expresses the wish that all Member States ... should set up similar national organisations so that they can cooperate with the European agency .
</s>
<s id="1273:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1273&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.20">
Now there have been recent and serious occurrences in Germany which show that every State must now set up a national food safety body and it is therefore all the more surprising that Italy , after setting up the agency , has now changed its mind for budget reasons .
</s>
<s id="1273:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1273&start=00.01.21&end=00.01.26">
Food safety ehm should not be halted by budgetary limits .
</s>
<s id="1273:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1273&start=00.01.26&end=00.01.26">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1274" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="149" duration="short" durations="71.0" speed="slow" speedwm="125.9" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Question Hour with the President of the Commission" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Alfano Sonia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="178" duration="short" durations="80.0" speed="medium" speedwm="133.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1274:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.18">
Directive 2001 establish the definition of renewable forms of energy before then establishes which are ehm e- open to public incentives .
</s>
<s id="1274:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.24">
Now , obviously we also have to look at the question of the bi- non-biodegradable nature of waste .
</s>
<s id="1274:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.00.25&end=00.00.38">
Italy has increased the ehm energy bills to ehm citizens and has boosted the ehm building of ehm incinerators , which is bad for health and it 's not an answer for management of waste .
</s>
<s id="1274:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.52">
With reference to these incentives , there have been 2 infringement procedures and , despite formal legislative intervention , in Italy , ehm incineration of waste is still being driven ehm and ... as we 've seen .
</s>
<s id="1274:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.01">
Obviously , I think it might be difficult to remember the details of the ehm situation and that 's why I 've provided a question in writing .
</s>
<s id="1274:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.11">
It 's not possible to ehm encourage incineration of non-biodegradable waste and there are no derogations provided in that direction .
</s>
<s id="1274:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.21">
Also , I think it 's a bit inconsistent that the waste Directive puts the ehm question of incineration as one possibility of ehm using of getting rid of waste ...
</s>
<s id="1274:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1274&start=00.01.23&end=00.01.24">
The Chair interrupts .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1275" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="192" duration="short" durations="89.0" speed="slow" speedwm="129.4" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Patients' rights in cross border healthcare" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rossi Oreste" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="181" duration="short" durations="89.0" speed="slow" speedwm="122.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1275:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.32">
Colleagues , initially the Directive ehm presented critical points , but when it was discussed in the commission and trialogue agreed came to an agreement on an overall balanced text which takes account of the need for quality in health security , the general principle of reimbursements and preventive care , also of trans- a cross-border cooperation on dealing with rare diseases and e-medicine .
</s>
<s id="1275:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.00.32&end=00.00.43">
The objective which we were striving towards was to recognise for all patients the right to cross-border healthcare , but avoiding ehm medical tourism .
</s>
<s id="1275:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.00.44&end=00.00.54">
Obviously we need services provided for citizens sh- other Member States but these services have quite rightly to be paid for the patient's country of origin .
</s>
<s id="1275:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.00.54&end=00.01.03">
Now we have to bring in the obligation for Member States to guarantee these entry levels of healthcare , we would have liked to see that but it was n't possible .
</s>
<s id="1275:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.18">
Now ehm obviously we will vote in favour , co- ' cause efforts have been made to to improve the text and that applies also on the other text up for vote ehm on Alzheimer's for example and ...
</s>
<s id="1275:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.01.20&end=00.01.28">
I think that we have to look at integration between the various different existing policies which is the aim of these reports .
</s>
<s id="1275:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1275&start=00.01.28&end=00.01.36">
The aim is to support the need for greater coordination between Member States in the exclusive interest of citizens .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1276" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="207" duration="short" durations="99.0" speed="slow" speedwm="125.5" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Patients' rights in cross border healthcare" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Ronzulli Licia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="199" duration="short" durations="96.0" speed="slow" speedwm="124.4" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1276:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.09">
Thank you President .
</s>
<s id="1276:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.25">
Well , this has taken years , legally speaking , and tomorrow , finally , we will have the Directive which give ehm a sound , legal basis for eu- those European citizens who have to go abroad every year to have appropriate medical care .
</s>
<s id="1276:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.00.25&end=00.00.38">
It will allow all patients , not only the better off and the best informed , to benefit from the rights which have been recognised so many years now in rulings from the Court of Justice .
</s>
<s id="1276:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.56">
Through the national contact points , they will be able to have access to ehm trans-border care and that will no longer be a leap in the dark , which ehm many patients have had to do so often facing bureaucratic , linguistic and economic problems whilst already facing a serious illness .
</s>
<s id="1276:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.00.57&end=00.01.12">
In terms of hospital care , maybe the patient can deci- be asked to ehm request prior authorisation for healthcare aboard and that 's necessary in terms of the stability of the entire national health systems .
</s>
<s id="1276:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.25">
Maybe we could have done more to protect patients' rights , for example , on the preventive notification system , which will allow Member States to pre-empt medical spending , not only on involuntary basis .
</s>
<s id="1276:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.01.25&end=00.01.46">
And allow me finally to ehm stress how enthusiastic I am ehm at this debate which I think has really drawn on one single common denomina- denominator , that is put an end to this calvary for thousands of patients across Europe , apparently now we have reached that point .
</s>
<s id="1276:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1276&start=00.01.46&end=00.01.47">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1277" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="114" duration="short" durations="60.0" speed="slow" speedwm="114.0" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Patients' rights in cross border healthcare" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Iacolino Salvatore" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="118" duration="short" durations="62.0" speed="slow" speedwm="114.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN73" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1277:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1277&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.21">
Thank you President , ehm this is certainly ehm a ehm b- ehm an overall ehm provision , an important and ehm structuring one and the rapporteur deserves our sincere applause .
</s>
<s id="1277:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1277&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.32">
This is a cross-border provision , in other words it gives freedom of choice to patients , closely linked to the freedom of movement in other words that typifies the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1277:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1277&start=00.00.33&end=00.00.46">
This is a mobility which is now recognised both for rare diseases and for the highly specialised diseases that need a early response .
</s>
<s id="1277:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1277&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.57">
Ehm so this is all part of the right to health in what is now of course an increasingly electronic ehm system of treatment .
</s>
<s id="1277:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1277&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.08">
And , what 's more , this is a measure ehm which in the future could be accompanied with a European form of accreditation ehm .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1278" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="111" duration="short" durations="60.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.0" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Patients' rights in cross border healthcare" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Pirillo Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="118" duration="short" durations="58.0" speed="slow" speedwm="122.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN73" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1278:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1278&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.31">
Thank you President , ehm access to cross-border healthcare in Europe has so far been subject to a number of limitations , long waiting lists or a complex system of refunds ... or indeed difficulty in identifying who 's responsible for providing ehm p- p- ehm post-operational care .
</s>
<s id="1278:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1278&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.45">
So this is an important step forward that we now have , it clarifies a lot of the administration , it improves cooperation between Member States and it improves ehm quality and safety standards for patients .
</s>
<s id="1278:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1278&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.58">
Now patients will be able to find out what care is available in another Member State , what procedures they have to go through , ehm what appeal procedures there are and so on .
</s>
<s id="1278:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1278&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.07">
And this is based no longer on economic ehm capacity , but on a genuine right of informed choice .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1279" date="2011-01-18" length="medium" lengthw="674" duration="long" durations="363.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.4" delivery="mixed" topic="Health" topicspec="European initiative on Alzheimer's disease and other dementias Asthma inhalers" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mazzoni Erminia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="673" duration="long" durations="362.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.5" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN74" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1279:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.31">
Thank you President , I too share your ehm puzzlement about the logic of combining this report this question with the previous report , but the important thing is that the House should consider the subject ehm dealt with in my question that I tabled on behalf of the Petitions committee .
</s>
<s id="1279:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.00.32&end=00.00.44">
We raise a case of denied justice , justice denied to a small European country small European company because of the Commission's inertia from 1997 to today .
</s>
<s id="1279:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.00.44&end=00.00.48">
The Legal Affairs committee , which we asked for an opinion , agrees with this judgement .
</s>
<s id="1279:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.00.49&end=00.00.59">
What we 're talking about is a piece of medical equipment - an asthma inhaler in fact - ehm which was properly marketed in 1990 .
</s>
<s id="1279:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.21">
This comes under Directive ehm 94 ehm 93EEC , which says that conformity ehm type approval is a matter of self ehm certification by the producer and the national authorities ehm can then exercise a ehm a sample monitoring activity .
</s>
<s id="1279:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.01.21&end=00.01.47">
So the product was on the market for 6 years until 1996 and nobody ehm sampled it ehm nobody objected to it ehm at which point it was checked by the Upper Bavaria government authority , which then asked the Magdeburg commission to ehm revoke the licence to the given to the company .
</s>
<s id="1279:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.01.48&end=00.02.02">
December the same year , the Upper ehm Saxony ehm Health Ministry carried out this check and concluded that the product was entirely in line with the legal ehm requirements .
</s>
<s id="1279:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.02.04&end=00.02.25">
Ehm and raised doubts about the justification of the request coming from Upper Bavaria ... asking Upper Bavaria , if it still had doubts , to embark on the safeguard process that is contained in the Directive in question .
</s>
<s id="1279:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.02.26&end=00.02.44">
Then in the following years , a number of activities continued , but which are not documented , we only have hearsay accounts of , and then in ' 97 , suddenly , without any kind of communication to the producer , the Federal Ministry of Health decided to withdraw the product from the market .
</s>
<s id="1279:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.02.49&end=00.03.26">
This was at the end of ' 97 , procedure a- under Article 8 of the aforesaid Directive , but then it was shunted into a siding , because the consultations stage the consultation with the procedure never ha- with the producer never happened and the producer then in 2003 , considering that this ehm silence from the Ministry ... started to market the product again assuming that the objections to it had been dropped .
</s>
<s id="1279:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.03.26&end=00.03.36">
But , unhappily , in 2005 - still without any communication - the German authorities once again withdrew the product from the market .
</s>
<s id="1279:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.03.37&end=00.03.49">
But it needs to be specified that still today , despite repeated requests , no evidence has been produced to explain why the product had to be withdrawn from the market .
</s>
<s id="1279:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.03.49&end=00.04.09">
So , there have been no communication , ehm there has been no possibility of legitimate appeal for the producer and there have been serious economic consequences for him , because it 's now more than 15 years that he 's waiting he 's been waiting for a reply and he ca n't market his product in the meanwhile .
</s>
<s id="1279:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.04.10&end=00.04.33">
And in the course of the 6 years that the product was marketed - and we have seen evidence of this in the committee - in the course of those 6 years , considerable savings in public health expenditure were made , because it 's a much cheaper product than the competition , and progress was made in treating sufferers .
</s>
<s id="1279:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.04.35&end=00.04.40">
In 2008 , having exhausted all other possibilities , Mr Klein turned to the Petitions committee .
</s>
<s id="1279:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.04.42&end=00.04.44">
Ehm we started on the procedure in this ...
</s>
<s id="1279:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.04.45&end=00.05.17">
Parliament and , considering the very long delays that the petition had already suffered , we embarked on an informal consultation with the Commissioner asking for an earlier reply , because what the petitioner is asking for is simply a further confirmation that his product is in line with European legislation or , at least , he wants an order that he can take to a Court and appeal against and he has n't had any of this so far .
</s>
<s id="1279:18" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.05.19&end=00.05.55">
In the course of the debate in the Petitions committee , the European Commission unfortunately ev- evaded the questions once again , which is why the committee decided to take the matter to the Chamber and ehm to put on this question to the Commission , looking for clear answers , because there is no question that this whole matter raises serious doubts ehm about infringement of fundamental rights , not just through the Commission's inertia , but , above all , because ehm the petitioner , Mr Klein , ehm can not go to any Court .
</s>
<s id="1279:19" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1279&start=00.06.00&end=00.06.12">
So clear doubts arise about the ehm infringement of market rules and the protection of small businesses , which is why we should very much like to have a reply to the questions contained in this question .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1280" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="111" duration="short" durations="64.0" speed="slow" speedwm="104.1" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="European initiative on Alzheimer's disease and other dementias Asthma inhalers" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Bartolozzi Paolo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="125" duration="short" durations="64.0" speed="slow" speedwm="117.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1280:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1280&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.17">
Mr President , ladies and gentlemen ... neurodegenerative diseases , including Alzheimer , are a health priority for the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1280:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1280&start=00.00.18&end=00.00.32">
This disease has serious effects , not just health effects on the sufferer , but very considerable costs have to be ehm paid for have to be met for direct cure and informal cure .
</s>
<s id="1280:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1280&start=00.00.33&end=00.00.39">
Alzheimer is not just a matter for the sufferer , it involves all the people who look after the sufferers .
</s>
<s id="1280:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1280&start=00.00.41&end=00.01.11">
So , it becomes necessary to have a European response to this problem , an overall coordination between Member States , synergy of concerted actions , above all in the scientific and research field , as ... we need to push prevention much more and we need innovative cures , among others , and we need to exchange information between States on the ehm results that they 've achieved through their research .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1281" date="2011-01-18" length="medium" lengthw="587" duration="medium" durations="347.0" speed="slow" speedwm="101.5" delivery="mixed" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Question Time" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Tajani Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="European Commission" politgroup="NA">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="609" duration="medium" durations="346.0" speed="slow" speedwm="105.6" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1281:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.12">
Mr President ... ladies and gentlemen .
</s>
<s id="1281:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.00.16&end=00.01.05">
The European ehm tourism industry , like many others , has to face up to the ever greater challenge of globalisation and this is a challenge which the Commission has already stressed and addressed on a number of occasions , particularly in its communication ' Industrial policy in the era of globalisation ' and what 's more , on the 30th of June last year , the Commission passed a specific communication on tourism , which - in line with new with a ehm Lisbon ehm Treaty - puts forward a new consolidated framework to strengthen the competitiveness of the industry , the idea being to make European tourism a genuinely competitive , modern , stable and responsible industry .
</s>
<s id="1281:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.18">
A ehm favourable context for SMEs and ehm one-man companies one-person companies ehm in tourism is also part of this framework .
</s>
<s id="1281:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.28">
In order to meet this objective , we specified 3 actions , first , to encourage the competitiveness of the tourism industry within the Union ;
</s>
<s id="1281:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.35">
secondly , to foster the development of sustainable tourism , responsible , quality tourism ;
</s>
<s id="1281:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.01.35&end=00.01.51">
and thirdly , to consolidate the image and the profile of Europe as a set of sustainable , quality tourist destinations and , of course , ehm we need to exploit all the potential of the financial instruments available to the Union to develop tourism .
</s>
<s id="1281:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.01.52&end=00.02.04">
The initiatives th- to be promoted will have to give the industry the instruments so that it can adapt to the ehm challenge that faces it , and also so that it can develop in a sustainable and competitive way .
</s>
<s id="1281:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.02.06&end=00.02.32">
Specific measures , implementing measures will be brought forward to promote innovation in tourism , to encourage quality , to improve quality in tourism and to strengthen the skills of the staff in tourism , as we can not any longer regard tourism as an industry ... ehm run entirely by families ;
</s>
<s id="1281:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.02.33&end=00.02.37">
we have to think of a more modern and a more competitive form of tourism .
</s>
<s id="1281:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.02.39&end=00.02.54">
Let me give you a few examples of professional training that we have in mind : a way of adapting companies to ehm information technology , thus making them more competitiveness .
</s>
<s id="1281:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.02.55&end=00.03.13">
All of these proposals incidentally are to be included in the Commission's ehm communication , ehm ... ehm which is ehm d- being debated in Parliament - the rapporteur is present here this evening .
</s>
<s id="1281:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.03.14&end=00.03.45">
Ehm better use of the different ehm c- Community programmes , like Leonardo or the Competitiveness Framework Programme , Erasmus for young businessmen , European Social Fund , other programmes and , also , there is a strategy to promote the offer ehm the offer of a broad spectrum of a broad palette of the ehm forms of tourism and equally we will be trying to c- create in other ways a favourable context .
</s>
<s id="1281:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.03.45&end=00.04.13">
It also needs to be recalled that SMEs can benefit from other horizontal ehm offers of ehm finance , for example JEREMIE , which is a joint initiative by the ehm Commission and the European Investment Bank , which intends to improve access of SMEs to finance , through ehm venture capital , loans ehm and loan guarantees .
</s>
<s id="1281:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.04.14&end=00.04.30">
And lastly , I 'd remind us that SMEs in the tourism sector they are fully entitled to benefit from the ehm measures that intend to ehm improve the operational context for SMEs .
</s>
<s id="1281:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.04.31&end=00.04.37">
Parliament will be receiving the updated text on these measures in the next few weeks .
</s>
<s id="1281:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.04.38&end=00.05.14">
So , the Small Business Act ehm is also going to be able to protect and encourage SMEs in tourism ... which have a remarkable potential ehm to develop ehm a sector that ehm has to develop in the next few years and I 'm absolutely convinced that a European policy , as envisaged in the Treaty , can represent added value on top of the work that the European regions and Member States are already ehm excellently doing .
</s>
<s id="1281:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1281&start=00.05.15&end=00.05.46">
So I 'd like to assure the questioner ... that the ehm Commission ehm the Commission and I myself am committed to ensure that all SMEs can be supported and can be given better and easier access to Community financial instruments , in the overall context of a strategy ehm that wants to make ehm tourism into a linchpin of our industry .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1282" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="145" duration="short" durations="63.0" speed="medium" speedwm="138.1" delivery="mixed" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Question Time" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Fidanza Carlo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="148" duration="short" durations="63.0" speed="medium" speedwm="141.0" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1282:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1282&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.11">
Yes , now it is my turn , ehm sorry for the last time Mr President .
</s>
<s id="1282:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1282&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.23">
Ehm thank you Mr President , I 'm grateful to Mr Balcytis for his question , which centres our debate on questions which we 'll be addressing in the next few months , with the report ehm that I am drawing up .
</s>
<s id="1282:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1282&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.41">
Ehm first of all , I 'm grateful to Vice-President Tajani for the very strong impulse that he 's given to the new European tourism policy that is contained in the that is envisaged in the Lisbon Treaty , with the communication from June and the implementing plan tabled only a few weeks ago .
</s>
<s id="1282:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1282&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.52">
These 2 things concentrate attention on SMEs ehm as a contribution to the competitiveness t- of the sector , particularly as regards innovation and training .
</s>
<s id="1282:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1282&start=00.00.52&end=00.01.10">
On finance , there are 2 lines to act on : first of all , we need to make the existing funds more available and more easily easy to recognise and , secondly , Parliament - I 'm concluding , President - there are 14 million there are 14 million specific invend- in- inventions for tourism policy .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1283" date="2011-01-18" length="medium" lengthw="609" duration="medium" durations="301.0" speed="slow" speedwm="121.4" delivery="impromptu" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Question Time" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Tajani Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="European Commission" politgroup="NA">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="619" duration="medium" durations="303.0" speed="slow" speedwm="122.6" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1283:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.23">
Thank you Mr President , I 'm grateful to Mr Balcytis because he gave me a chance to speak about a subject that I 'm particularly keen on , ehm among the subjects that I 'm responsible for in the Commission .
</s>
<s id="1283:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.31">
Tourism , together with ehm space and industry industrial policies , ehm are my priorities .
</s>
<s id="1283:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.00.32&end=00.01.03">
Now , ehm to respond more precisely to your question , over and above the political the policy initiatives that I have been pursuing ehm ever since I became ehm Commissioner , one of these things is what Mr Fidanza mentioned : ehm when there was n't a Community policy for tourism Community ehm competence for tourism before the Lisbon Treaty , there were n't the necessary funds ehm to provide Community assistance for a major tourist action .
</s>
<s id="1283:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.10">
There were things like Calypso , ehm there were regional initiatives in Spain and all of these were good things .
</s>
<s id="1283:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.01.12&end=00.01.38">
But , if I 've understood ehm right Mr Fidanza's message , in the report that he will be putting to Parliament , there 's going to be support , for the idea that the next financial perspectives should increase funds for tourism policy and that could then be fitted into the 8th framework research programme , or framework programme ehm with a relevant budget line .
</s>
<s id="1283:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.01.39&end=00.01.46">
Ehm but , of course , it 's difficult to give specific replies as long as you do n't have a financial instrument available to you .
</s>
<s id="1283:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.01.46&end=00.01.51">
Having said that , of course , ehm we will still move in a very determined way .
</s>
<s id="1283:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.01.51&end=00.02.11">
As you know , great many initiatives have already been adopted , Belgian Presidency o- organised a major event in in ehm , and the Hungarian Presidency is going to organise a major event ehm - and a few days ago we had a first ehm discussion in Budapest about it .
</s>
<s id="1283:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.02.13&end=00.02.29">
And I am also happy that Mr Balcytis raised the issue of tourism in the Baltic : tourism is not just a matter for Mediterranean countries - ehm Spain , ehm France , Italy , Greece and Malta .
</s>
<s id="1283:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.02.30&end=00.02.42">
It 's a very important resource for the whole of the European Union , including for the countries of Central and Eastern Europe , which have beauties and have a potential ehm that can be developed .
</s>
<s id="1283:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.02.43&end=00.03.12">
And as regards the Baltic countries , one of the countries one of the subjects that needs to be w- is addressed in the text approved on the 30th of June last year is the new middle class ehm in the Russian Federation , ehm which is millions and millions of people ... who now want to embark on tourism and they want to , in other words , leave their own country .
</s>
<s id="1283:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.03.12&end=00.03.17">
For that purpose , of course , there are visa problems , as there are with China .
</s>
<s id="1283:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.03.18&end=00.03.51">
But the European Commission's desire and ministers for tourism's desire is to solve this problem ehm in terms of the Russian tourism potential as well as the Chinese potential , in order faster to ensure ehm that we can receive in our countries and the Baltic countries , of course , are nearest to the Russian Federation , so they can expect ehm to receive ehm a lot of tourist visits from this emerging middle class , which should bring them economic advantage .
</s>
<s id="1283:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.03.52&end=00.04.19">
And this is ehm in the centre of our work in favour of tou- tourism , and I 'm happy to know that many ministers of different countries - a few weeks ago , in London , I met the new British ehm touris- tourism minister - I 'm happy to know that even grea- Great Britain as well is committed to support the new Union tourism policy ehm so is France .
</s>
<s id="1283:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.04.19&end=00.04.39">
So we 'd have to identify some e- some entry ehm ports ehm and I think that Commissioner Vassiliou wanted to put in in the text today approved today about sport , ehm for example there 's the big Olympic opportunity coming up in London , which has to be seen as a major European opportunity .
</s>
<s id="1283:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.04.40&end=00.04.51">
In other words , we need to see that every European country has a porch where ehm tourists can enter and then they can visit the country and , having done that , they can move on to other European countries .
</s>
<s id="1283:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1283&start=00.04.52&end=00.05.10">
That 's the added value that the Commission ehm can offer , and Parliament's support will be decisive , I believe , and I 'm grateful ehm for your attention , particularly ehm for the future debate on tourism policy , ehm and also on the budgetary side of that .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1284" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="125" duration="short" durations="79.0" speed="slow" speedwm="94.9" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Situation in Haiti one year after the earthquake humanitarian aid and reconstruction" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rinaldi Niccol√≤" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="169" duration="short" durations="77.0" speed="medium" speedwm="131.7" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1284:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1284&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.51">
Thank you Commissioner , colleagues , Haiti is very much a different case , because if you 're thinking about the anniversary of a disaster , you are normally thinking of victims or elections , but there 's nothing to think back to in Haiti . 1 ... year after the earthquake , we 've had a earthquake in aid , in health , in cholera , elections at the worst possible time , and an earthquake historically , where the ex-dictator goes back on a holiday to have a look around .
</s>
<s id="1284:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1284&start=00.00.52&end=00.00.58">
We were there with the Development commissioner , we saw the splendid work and thank you for it .
</s>
<s id="1284:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1284&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.07">
But we need better political sponsorship from the international community , with clear deadlines and direct management of some of the aid .
</s>
<s id="1284:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1284&start=00.01.08&end=00.01.16">
But this has to be balanced with proper involvement of local energy and people , then often cut out .
</s>
<s id="1284:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1284&start=00.01.16&end=00.01.27">
National governing institutions in Haiti hold sway rather than involvement of local communities and the international community .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1285" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="263" duration="medium" durations="156.0" speed="slow" speedwm="101.2" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Bizzotto Mara" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="371" duration="medium" durations="154.0" speed="medium" speedwm="144.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1285:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.22">
Thank you , the situation in Campania , particularly in Naples , is known to the whole world sadly for many years and the European Union has dealt with this variously .
</s>
<s id="1285:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.41">
But given that paradoxical , third-world situation , I 'd like to know what the Commission's consequences are with regard to Italian law and what sanctions will be applied if the waste crisis in Campania is n't terminated shortly .
</s>
<s id="1285:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.54">
If the Commission would look closely at the information of European funds managed in Campania for an integrated waste collection and disposal system .
</s>
<s id="1285:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.05">
Only when you are talking about emergency , are you talking about drastic situations , but the- they have to be sorted out in re- reasonable time .
</s>
<s id="1285:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.11">
If there 's been emergency for 15 years on s- more , something 's not working .
</s>
<s id="1285:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.33">
The Italian government 's done what it can to sort out this waste collection and disposal cycle , but ehm round Naples there are tonnes and tonnes of waste to be disposed of by the Campania local authorities and they 're not able or willing to sort this out .
</s>
<s id="1285:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.01.33&end=00.01.58">
There 's no doubt that the situation in Naples and Campania is a situation that 's been notably ... communes and regions with regard to operating a proper waste cycle , ehm separation and operation of waste , but this is not ... the problem of the Italian government .
</s>
<s id="1285:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.01.58&end=00.02.10">
The Italian government could have sent in the army - it did a few weeks ago and has done before - to operate turbines turbines that had not been properly operated .
</s>
<s id="1285:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.02.10&end=00.02.12">
It 's not the Italian government's fault .
</s>
<s id="1285:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.02.12&end=00.02.16">
It it it 's different in the rest of ...
</s>
<s id="1285:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.02.17&end=00.02.24">
Italy , such as in Veneto , where we 've had differentiated cycling with a high yield level for years .
</s>
<s id="1285:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1285&start=00.02.25&end=00.02.46">
It means that the responsibility is due to local administration in Campania and operation with criminal elements that are obtaining big ehm profits through the in- infiltration of the Camorra into local authorities and government .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1286" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="346" duration="medium" durations="213.0" speed="slow" speedwm="97.5" delivery="mixed" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mazzoni Erminia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="462" duration="medium" durations="213.0" speed="medium" speedwm="130.1" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1286:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.34">
Thank you President and thank you for the Commissioner for pointing out that the Petitions committee has been actively involved on behalf of the Parliament with the political role responsibly dealing with this situation , transparently and involving citizens in a proper and responsible dialogue .
</s>
<s id="1286:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.49">
As the regional executive said in March this year , there has been dialogue with the European Commission and I 'm sure that this was different from previous years .
</s>
<s id="1286:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.00.49&end=00.01.03">
Nothing staggering , but people becoming responsible for a drastic situation that has ehm become stronger over the last 15 years through inaction or insufficient action .
</s>
<s id="1286:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.16">
Italy was condemned by the Court of Justice in March 2010 for facts going back to 2007 , but the situation has changed since then .
</s>
<s id="1286:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.16&end=00.01.30">
The regional assessor has been 3 times to Brussels and has already done a fair amount of the programme put out during a hearing in July in the peti- Petitions committee .
</s>
<s id="1286:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.31&end=00.01.35">
Quickly , listing , these ehm special waste programmes ;
</s>
<s id="1286:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.36&end=00.01.39">
solid urban waste programmes ;
</s>
<s id="1286:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.40&end=00.01.48">
the last plan with the corrections put forward by the Commission , approved by the 30th of April , as stated .
</s>
<s id="1286:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.48&end=00.01.56">
The plan 's already partly put through and operating , with the Acerra re-treatment system ;
</s>
<s id="1286:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.56&end=00.01.58">
the system in Salerno ;
</s>
<s id="1286:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.01.58&end=00.02.03">
n- Naples East being subject to contract ;
</s>
<s id="1286:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.02.03&end=00.02.33">
7 waste recovery and composting plants , 1 for ehm aerobic air management and 100 ... other sets of waste management ... areas in 5 provinces to dispose of accumulated waste and agreements with 5 regional councils for temporary storage , throughout the plan is carried out .
</s>
<s id="1286:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.02.35&end=00.02.51">
Some resources being taken out of the regional fund and , as Mr Buccelli said in the Environment committee , times for complying with the judgement are between 12 and 24 months , so we 're well on time .
</s>
<s id="1286:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.02.52&end=00.03.13">
The Commission discretionally can look for an extension realistically in accordance with the advancement of our work and I think we 're well within time as stated by the petitioners and i- i- it 's not ... likely that there will be a need for further monetary sanctions .
</s>
<s id="1286:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.03.13&end=00.03.22">
We 're well on time and I hope this debate is n't being used ... to work against the institutions and political parties .
</s>
<s id="1286:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.03.22&end=00.03.41">
If it 's a proper debate to help Campania to come up with a solution to an old problem , then the resolutions that might go through in February could be common ones , otherwise , it will be another waste of time and it will make the situation simply worse .
</s>
<s id="1286:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1286&start=00.03.41&end=00.03.42">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1287" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="238" duration="medium" durations="149.0" speed="slow" speedwm="95.8" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Pirillo Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="272" duration="medium" durations="148.0" speed="slow" speedwm="110.3" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1287:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.24">
Thank you , the deep-seated crises that we 've seen with the waste cycle in Campania are not wearari- wearing just because of the consequences on the and the effect on local people .
</s>
<s id="1287:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.47">
As European institutions , we may intervene to stop this going on further , dragging on further , with safeguards from local authorities ... making sure they 're taken to task until they come forward with a credible solution to this awful emergency in Campania .
</s>
<s id="1287:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.00.48&end=00.00.54">
But people have talked about this waste em- emergency , without knowing about the situation .
</s>
<s id="1287:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.00.54&end=00.01.13">
Campania was asked to put forward a regional plan in 2010 , now postponed to 2011 , and the situation is im- not manageable if there is further postponement , given that there 's continuation of organised crime making money .
</s>
<s id="1287:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.01.14&end=00.01.25">
The Italian government , with a decree-law in 2009 , said that the emergency was closed and handed over the wis- waste cycle to the provinces .
</s>
<s id="1287:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.01.27&end=00.01.44">
In an area such as Napoli , where most of the people of Campania live , only the regions can apply properly the measures that are required .
</s>
<s id="1287:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.01.44&end=00.01.54">
There are greater efforts made and a lot of results in differentiation of waste , with moneys that have gone in there .
</s>
<s id="1287:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.01.55&end=00.02.04">
Listening to local administrations is particularly important : firstly , to take a general and overall view on the ground .
</s>
<s id="1287:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.02.07&end=00.02.29">
This is where you can see how the waste is disposed of , it would need no- new incinerators , but ehm looking at Terzigno and the Quarry in there and the dumping and landfill , we are looking at a paralysis of the entire waste cycle system in Campania .
</s>
<s id="1287:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1287&start=00.02.30&end=00.02.37">
We will wait for the Commission's reply and we will wait for the region of Campania to put forward a proper programme .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1288" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="187" duration="short" durations="118.0" speed="slow" speedwm="95.1" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Alfano Sonia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="250" duration="short" durations="117.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.2" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1288:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.10&end=00.00.20">
Well , notwithstanding the Italian government's ehm propaganda , this is a structural problem not resolved in Campania .
</s>
<s id="1288:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.31">
You just need to take stock of one thing : the people of Campania are still living there and dying along with this waste .
</s>
<s id="1288:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.33&end=00.00.42">
And there are great responsibilities there , but this can not be offloaded on citizens , who are living unhealthy lives .
</s>
<s id="1288:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.49">
The European Union has to make sure that its intervention is quick or it wo n't work .
</s>
<s id="1288:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.51&end=00.00.56">
There should be no more incinerators , they 're a spot of waste disposal .
</s>
<s id="1288:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.00.57&end=00.01.17">
The was- waste is turned into ash , which is fatal and ... the waste Directive says that this is the last possible form but with other options that wo n't work against citizen's health and will create dro- job .
</s>
<s id="1288:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.29">
Given Mafia involvement , particularly in the waste cycle , this has been particularly in the south , rather than in the north , of the region in the last few years .
</s>
<s id="1288:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.43">
So , Commission , how you are going to act to stop this working against citizen's health and how you are going to stop citizens being subject to decisions that are going to affect their regions ?
</s>
<s id="1288:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.01.44&end=00.01.53">
Are you going to immediately have a register for violation against the entire region ?
</s>
<s id="1288:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1288&start=00.01.53&end=00.02.06">
And what about the provision in 2008 on the incentives for incinerators , where clearly were against the Community provisions on State aid ?
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1289" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="108" duration="short" durations="71.0" speed="slow" speedwm="91.3" delivery="mixed" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rossi Oreste" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="172" duration="short" durations="68.0" speed="medium" speedwm="151.8" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="NA" gender="NA" native="NA">
<s id="1289:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.21">
Thank you , th- the waste disposal system has to involve differentiation of waste , recycling and only incineration at the end .
</s>
<s id="1289:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.27">
I would ehm point out that the fault is not in the north or the south ;
</s>
<s id="1289:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.33">
ehm th- the minister was from the Green party previously .
</s>
<s id="1289:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.46">
Ehm for decades , people have talked about this problem around Naples and there is an emergency situation now , but the responsibility is from the north of Italy .
</s>
<s id="1289:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.00.47&end=00.01.09">
You you 're now talking about the waste going north of Naples , but this is just wrong , because , obviously , previous local administrations ... have allowed organised crime to make illegal disposals of waste and have n't prepared for disposal sufficiently .
</s>
<s id="1289:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1289&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.20">
So the people in Campania and Naples have regionally voted for incapable administrators , that is the truth .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1290" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="191" duration="short" durations="116.0" speed="slow" speedwm="98.8" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rivellini Crescenzio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="230" duration="short" durations="114.0" speed="slow" speedwm="121.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1290:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.34">
Thank you President and thank you to Mr Seeber and other people for entrusting me with this speech , but I must stress that in Campania a very positive activity is on the way and I think ... recourse to former Article 260 to obtain a fine is simply political use .
</s>
<s id="1290:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.00.35&end=00.00.50">
We already have a special refuse programme with an integrated waste cycle programme , we 've put forward a programme on differentiated waste and we 've started initiatives to cut the total amount of produce waste down .
</s>
<s id="1290:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.00.51&end=00.01.23">
In Salerno , then , incinerator 's being tendered out for and there 's publication of a tender for an incinerator in the east of Naples , Napoli Est , not just to clear up the city , but to organise an integrated waste cycle with differentiated waste collection , cutting of waste , the used use of modern systems to get rid of ' ecoballs ' and to dispose properly of old waste .
</s>
<s id="1290:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.01.23&end=00.01.42">
Ehm the people who are culpable are the former administrators in camini- c- Campania on the left , particularly , the Greens , but people in the north of Italy , who 've used organised crime to get rid of their ehm waste , as well their toxic waste .
</s>
<s id="1290:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.01.43&end=00.01.49">
So , without prejudice , I would u- urge that we work for and not against ...
</s>
<s id="1290:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1290&start=00.01.52&end=00.02.04">
Campania for ideological and political reasons , but seeing that by fining people in Campania you 're not going to solve the emergency , are you ?
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1291" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="107" duration="short" durations="75.0" speed="slow" speedwm="85.6" delivery="impromptu" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="De Magistris Luigi" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="155" duration="short" durations="74.0" speed="slow" speedwm="125.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1291:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1291&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.52">
Well , ehm following the lies of Berlusconi's government , going back to 2008 saying that the waste problem was over , it 's good for the European Union has blocked Italian funds until a waste cycle programme which is eco-compatible has been put forward with waste s- recycling and composting , rather than c- Caldoro's idea , which is uncontrolled waste in Taverna del Re and ti- Terzigno - in the Vesuvius National Park - nor ehm people being killed or having health problems and tumours .
</s>
<s id="1291:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1291&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.23">
Over the last 13 years we 've s- ehm seen extra support for crime , for political crime , for large-scale entrepreneurs and the Camorra , with criminalisation ehm for local authorities , people , who are living on the ground , as the Italian government has done to stop people defending natural territory and regions in Italy .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1292" date="2011-01-18" length="long" lengthw="83" duration="short" durations="55.0" speed="slow" speedwm="90.5" delivery="mixed" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Speroni Francesco Enrico" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="long" lengthw="67" duration="short" durations="54.0" speed="slow" speedwm="74.4" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1292:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1292&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.21">
Thank you President , a centralist and bureaucratic Europe is n't distinguishing between regions and a- administrative arrangements within the Member States .
</s>
<s id="1292:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1292&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.30">
Responsibilities for the disastrous waste situation in Campania mainly lie with the citizens of Campania .
</s>
<s id="1292:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1292&start=00.00.30&end=00.00.54">
I 'm from Padano and I would reject these charges and I would ... inveigh against people who , in Campania , voted in local administrators who were incapable of solving this problem , and have continued to make the same mistake by voting them in one election after another .
</s>
<s id="1292:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1292&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.02">
W - we are prepared to help Campania , but we 're not going to accept the charges levied against us .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1293" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="202" duration="medium" durations="145.0" speed="slow" speedwm="83.6" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Baldassarre Raffaele" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="231" duration="medium" durations="142.0" speed="slow" speedwm="97.6" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1293:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1293&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.33">
Thank you , dear Commissioner , colleagues , in my speech I 'm not denying the seriousness of the situation which is the obvious consequence of political and administrative shortcomings , which still risks to strangle an entire city and region with its waste problem .
</s>
<s id="1293:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1293&start=00.00.33&end=00.01.02">
Mrs Lichtenberger , the ... emergency in Campania has awfully developed through the lack of ability of regional authorities and Naples administration on the left and with Green councillors , to make unpopular and bold choices to have a virtuous waste collection and disposal cycle .
</s>
<s id="1293:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1293&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.37">
The responsibility , the indecision , the political incompetence and ... the cursing and lying have marked political administration , but this period is over now and I would like to assure the oral question signers that the political situation has totally changed , the national government has appealed responsibly to the regional authorities to sort the emergency out .
</s>
<s id="1293:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1293&start=00.01.38&end=00.01.54">
Dealing with this with the people involved firmly to overcome ... o- 1 or 2 obstacles through people ehm not wanting waste in their own backyard .
</s>
<s id="1293:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1293&start=00.01.54&end=00.02.32">
There 's been a proper waste disposal and collection cycle with a proper differentiation of waste , proper incineration and proper differentiation plants and it would be counterproductive and just political to impose sanctions or prohibitions on institutions that are using Community and national funds in full cooperation with the EU to put a final closure on this awful historical situation in Naples and Campania .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1294" date="2011-01-18" length="short" lengthw="169" duration="short" durations="111.0" speed="slow" speedwm="91.4" delivery="read" topic="Environment" topicspec="Waste crisis in Campania" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Comi Lara" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="220" duration="short" durations="107.0" speed="slow" speedwm="123.4" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN45" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1294:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.10">
Dear Commissioner , dear colleagues , thank you ...
</s>
<s id="1294:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.22">
President , I clearly like to state in my speech that the waste crisis in Campania has greatly improved over recent years .
</s>
<s id="1294:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.43">
It has been complex and given rise to a lot of problems , and it takes time to reach a final solution , but the oral question here in- invokes the procedure under Article 260 , but it 's not a fine that 's going to solve the waste crisis in Campania , is it ?
</s>
<s id="1294:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.00.44&end=00.01.06">
We may then ehm be helping ... apply responsibility , but this responsibility has to be objective , resulting from application of violation of Community law ehm and subjective operation of the State .
</s>
<s id="1294:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.24">
But Italy has ... respected the obligations to cooperate and the Commission services are in close contact with the national government , regional and local authorities to follow the situation closely .
</s>
<s id="1294:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.01.24&end=00.01.28">
The clear commitment by Italy can not be denied .
</s>
<s id="1294:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1294&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.43">
