<text id="1301" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="177" duration="short" durations="83.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.0" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Matera Barbara" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="155" duration="short" durations="82.0" speed="slow" speedwm="113.4" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1301:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.15">
Thank you madam Chairman , I voted in favour of the question of ehm international adoption in the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1301:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.00.15&end=00.00.29">
International adoption I think is the best possibility of giving the possibility of providing a permanent family for those children for which a suitable or appropriate family ca n't be found in their country of origin .
</s>
<s id="1301:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.47">
Competition between cooperation between competent authorities in countries on international adoption is very important to ensure that the adoption is conducted in the interests of the child and in respect of their fundamental rights and that we avoid avoid ehm sale and trafficking of children .
</s>
<s id="1301:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.00.48&end=00.01.01">
We should simplify the procedures for international adoption , because all too often they are highly bureaucratic and they put families off from turning to adoption .
</s>
<s id="1301:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.01.02&end=00.01.08">
Romania is the only country in the European Union which has banned by law international adoption .
</s>
<s id="1301:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.01.08&end=00.01.30">
Today , t- there are about 20,000 orphans in the country , of which 40,000 are in orphanages and 30,000 are in foster homes and I feel that the European Commission should shed light on the situation in Romania , so that these abandoned children can be taken up in family nuclei through international adoption .
</s>
<s id="1301:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1301&start=00.01.30&end=00.01.31">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1302" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="143" duration="short" durations="61.0" speed="medium" speedwm="140.7" delivery="read" topic="Justice" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Ronzulli Licia" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="137" duration="short" durations="60.0" speed="medium" speedwm="137.0" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1302:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.19">
Thank you , all my thoughts right now go to the thousands of couples around the world who on a daily basis face the difficult needs to adopt .
</s>
<s id="1302:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.32">
Adoption is a value , a genuine expression of love which opens the doors to a new family for a child which unfortunately can not can no longer count on the affection of its own family .
</s>
<s id="1302:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.32&end=00.00.39">
They 're affected by ehm abandonment but they have the right to be brought up in a happy environment with people who can offer them a new life .
</s>
<s id="1302:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.39&end=00.00.46">
It 's our duty therefore to assist orphans so that th- the ehm a happy future is no longer utopic .
</s>
<s id="1302:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.50">
I think that we have to send out an immediate , strong signal .
</s>
<s id="1302:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.50&end=00.00.56">
We need to promote Community policies aimed at overcoming the difficulty faced by families .
</s>
<s id="1302:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1302&start=00.00.57&end=00.01.07">
Ehm bureaucratic foot-dragging , legislative obstacles can not and should not hamper the dream , the desire of a child to have a family and a happy future .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1303" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="136" duration="short" durations="66.0" speed="slow" speedwm="123.6" delivery="mixed" topic="Justice" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Muscardini Cristiana" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="116" duration="short" durations="67.0" speed="slow" speedwm="103.9" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1303:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1303&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.25">
Thank you ehm madam President , for many years in Europe we have been addressing this issue of international adoption and finally today's resolution is here trying to ehm give hope in what is becoming an ever more complex and difficult situation .
</s>
<s id="1303:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1303&start=00.00.25&end=00.00.44">
The arrival of new countries , rather than encouraging international adoption , has rendered it more and more difficult for certain couples to have access to children to whom they can offer a family , ehm who have been deprived in their own countries .
</s>
<s id="1303:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1303&start=00.00.44&end=00.00.58">
On the one hand , there is increasing bureaucracy which is hampering adoption of children , on the other , we have organ trafficking and child prostitution and that 's why I 'm in favour of this resolution .
</s>
<s id="1303:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1303&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.13">
We think it 's essential that we should speed up international adoption practices to ensure that finally we can have European adoption in order to give a future to so many children in so great in needs .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1304" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="194" duration="short" durations="83.0" speed="medium" speedwm="140.2" delivery="read" topic="Health" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mastella Clemente" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="209" duration="short" durations="83.0" speed="medium" speedwm="151.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN107" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1304:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.19">
Madam President , I vote in favour of this report because I feel that the communication to the Commission on Alzheimer's is very important .
</s>
<s id="1304:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.33">
I 'm saying this from experience , ' cause my father and my grandmother were ehm sufferers from Alzheimer's , I hope I 'm at the end of the genetic chain there , but we need to bring together various different European policies to provide support for citizens .
</s>
<s id="1304:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.55">
So , I think we have to renew our intentions to combat this form of disease and draw on what 's available in Europe , we have to try and break down disparity in terms of access to treatment , ehm we have also to work on early diagnosis and try and improve living conditions , improve knowledge about the disease and coordinate current research .
</s>
<s id="1304:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.00.56&end=00.01.01">
We 've got to ehm try and share good practices between Member States .
</s>
<s id="1304:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.01.02&end=00.01.20">
We would also like to have better coordination between Member States to provide a more solidarity-based ehm response to treatment to for such diseases , particularly Alzheimer's , and in order to support those people who support the sufferers , as well were they professionals or family members .
</s>
<s id="1304:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1304&start=00.01.21&end=00.01.31">
So , I think that we need to take steps in Europe , but that can only work on the condition that Member States give a prior- give priority to the definition of their own national priorities policies on this front .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1305" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="168" duration="short" durations="86.0" speed="slow" speedwm="117.2" delivery="read" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Provera Fiorello" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="165" duration="short" durations="87.0" speed="slow" speedwm="113.8" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN117" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1305:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.23">
Thank you President , the recent terrorist attacks in the Egypt and Iraq are criminal acts that , however tragic , represent only one aspect of the persecution of Christian communities throughout the world and in particular in the Middle East .
</s>
<s id="1305:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.46">
The most worrying aspect from an institutional standpoint is the systematic limitation of Christians' rights as citizens , which means that , for example , they are not allowed to build churches , ehm to ehm accede to public office or military ehm positions or have freedom of worship .
</s>
<s id="1305:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.00.46&end=00.00.55">
The 2 things together - terrorism and discrimination - mean that hundreds of thousands of citizens are obliged to migrate from these countries .
</s>
<s id="1305:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.03">
In Iraq , for example , 60 percent of the Christians have been obliged ehm to seek asylum and we are talking about 600,000 people .
</s>
<s id="1305:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.08">
The European Parliament fights for the rights of peoples to migrate .
</s>
<s id="1305:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.14">
In this instance , entire communities are denied the right to live in their own country .
</s>
<s id="1305:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.01.16&end=00.01.26">
Terrorism , that seeks the expulsion of Christianity from Arab countries , requires instruments , ehm that are even military , to prevent them .
</s>
<s id="1305:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.01.26&end=00.01.32">
But Europe , ehm which is historically Christian and that is a great defender of human rights , must take action .
</s>
<s id="1305:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1305&start=00.01.33&end=00.01.35">
The Chair interrupts .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1306" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="277" duration="medium" durations="127.0" speed="medium" speedwm="130.9" delivery="mixed" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mauro Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="240" duration="medium" durations="125.0" speed="slow" speedwm="115.2" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN118" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1306:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.25">
Thank you President , ehm Commissioner , I wish to thank you ehm profoundly for the contents of your contribution , because the purpose of this resolution is to ensure greater protection for religious minorities in everybody's interest .
</s>
<s id="1306:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.00.26&end=00.01.04">
However , with the same frankness , ehm but in all friendly friendship , I would like to point out that , if you have the patience to read the text that you have already read , you will realise that ehm the adjective ' Christian ' has never been used in what you said and this struck me , because in our institutions it creates some note of embarrassment and by so doing we f- fall into the trap of the fundamentalists , who tend to identify the presence of Christians in the Middle East and in other parts of the world ehm as ehm the rich of ehm Europe .
</s>
<s id="1306:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.12">
But my friends , my Palestinian f- Christians are Arabs , they think in Arabic , they love their country , they love their history and they love their culture .
</s>
<s id="1306:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.01.12&end=00.01.29">
So , I would ask you , ehm h- High Representative , should n't we ehm look ehm critically into our ehm consciences and see how we 've approached this topic so far , because we need ehm to be frank .
</s>
<s id="1306:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.01.30&end=00.01.49">
We need ehm to call hatred for Hebrews as anti-Semitism , or and hatred for Christians we also need to describe in appropriate manner , because only in this manner will we manage to involve all those people who in those countries embrace freedom and justice .
</s>
<s id="1306:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.01.50&end=00.01.52">
I would ask you for this and I would ask you to be ehm concrete .
</s>
<s id="1306:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.01.52&end=00.02.12">
We 're now going to ehm validate the agreement on Iraq , together with the principles of ehm trade , let us insert ehm certain laws considered they will because in exchange for rights there may be economic advantages , let 's act in the interests of everybody and let 's do it quickly , because the world is waiting for a signal for Europe .
</s>
<s id="1306:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1306&start=00.02.12&end=00.02.13">
Thank you very much .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1307" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="323" duration="medium" durations="136.0" speed="medium" speedwm="142.5" delivery="read" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Milana Guido" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="330" duration="medium" durations="137.0" speed="medium" speedwm="144.5" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN123" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1307:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.27">
Thank you President , thank you High Representative , it is important that the condemnation of these attacks and the demand for urgent measures to protect Christians throughout the world be related to the more general ehm request for respect for religion , of conscience and thought .
</s>
<s id="1307:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.45">
There is no difference of ehm killing somebody who ehm is attending mass or killing somebody who 's condemned for adultery , because part of a majority that is either Christian or Hebrew or Jewish or Arabic , or because one has been born in a particular place and not because one now practises a religion .
</s>
<s id="1307:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.00.45&end=00.00.53">
And the right to freedom and coexistence is universally recognised by international conventions and by ehm humanist culture .
</s>
<s id="1307:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.00.53&end=00.00.58">
Instead , the world is being divided up between those who defend human rights and those who wish to wipe them out .
</s>
<s id="1307:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.07">
Only an ehm an openness to dialogue , an attitude opposed to any f- ehm forms of extremism can provide a basis for identity and values .
</s>
<s id="1307:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.01.08&end=00.01.15">
A failure to respect these ehm leads to an exodus of entire communities from their historical places of residence .
</s>
<s id="1307:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.01.16&end=00.01.34">
There is an enormous amount of work to be done ehm by Europe ehm from a political , social , cultural standpoint and we urgently ask the Council and the Commission and the High Representative ehm to adopt clear guidelines in our relations with th- third countries in the framework of the new External Action Service .
</s>
<s id="1307:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.01.34&end=00.01.46">
Even bilateral agreements so should be paying more attention ehm to freedom of worship and , more generally speaking , human rights , a failure to respect of which is should be a reason ehm for not implementing these agreements .
</s>
<s id="1307:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.01.47&end=00.02.00">
I think ehm that ehm eu- that ehm religious ehm questions frequently goes beyond ehm tolerance and leads to wars , where religion ehm is a ehm complex part of conflict .
</s>
<s id="1307:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.02.00&end=00.02.05">
We in Europe too see acts of ehm intolerance .
</s>
<s id="1307:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.02.05&end=00.02.17">
Ehm our cities are experiencing multiculturalism ehm that brings with it traditions and religious values that must be respected and for which we must ensure freedom of expression .
</s>
<s id="1307:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.02.17&end=00.02.20">
There is no alternative , therefore , to dialogue and ehm mutual respect .
</s>
<s id="1307:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.02.20&end=00.02.21">
It is important ...
</s>
<s id="1307:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1307&start=00.02.21&end=00.02.24">
The Chair interrupts , thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1308" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="183" duration="short" durations="100.0" speed="slow" speedwm="109.8" delivery="read" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rinaldi Niccol√≤" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="183" duration="short" durations="93.0" speed="slow" speedwm="118.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN06" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1308:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.22">
Oh thank you ehm cam- President , High Representatives , the destiny of Christians in the Middle East - ehm Copti ehm ' Copts' means ' Egyptians ' in Egypt - and they have been in the region for many centuries .
</s>
<s id="1308:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.34">
But let us ehm not ehm fall into the mistakes that the ehm press makes , that is that we 're talking about they talk about clash of civilisation or class of clash of religions .
</s>
<s id="1308:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.50">
Now , a former farmer in Egypt who 3 times a week took milk to his home and he was standing at the door and he was crying and he said ' Said Akbar , Said Akbar ' , which means ' the old w- ehm wise man ' .
</s>
<s id="1308:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.00.50&end=00.00.56">
He ehm he was telling Christians that Karol Wojtyla had died those days .
</s>
<s id="1308:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.00.56&end=00.01.04">
He was a simple Muslim who fully represented the reciprocal respect of the peoples around the Mediterranean .
</s>
<s id="1308:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.17">
This is an interesting episode , a thermometer of the situation in Egypt , hapt- happened in exactly the same place where Copts Coptic Christians were attacked over Christma- Christmas .
</s>
<s id="1308:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.01.17&end=00.01.29">
They need to be ehm protected , protected from fundamen- fundamentalists and terrorists and ehm foreign policy in the European Union must must ehm continue .
</s>
<s id="1308:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.30">
Thank you .
</s>
<s id="1308:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.01.31&end=00.01.45">
European foreign policy must not ehm fear away from ehm speaking out , must show goodwill and democratic processes .
</s>
<s id="1308:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1308&start=00.01.45&end=00.01.46">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1309" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="145" duration="short" durations="67.0" speed="slow" speedwm="129.9" delivery="mixed" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Borghezio Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="140" duration="short" durations="66.0" speed="slow" speedwm="127.3" delivery="mixed">
<interpreter id="EN123" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1309:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.26">
Vice-Prepr- Representative , High Representative , in the ehm representative effort of European politics , there is a word which is taboo , which is ehm Christianphobia and yet , for some years now , we have heard of the tragic and serious news of the persecution of Christians in various ehm continents .
</s>
<s id="1309:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.00.26&end=00.00.29">
Well , Europe 's got to wake up and open its eyes .
</s>
<s id="1309:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.51">
It 's got to send out clear messages , for example what we were expecting from lady Ashton was ... and she might have taken up the words of ehm Pope Benedict who , a few days ago , said that the denial of ehm religious freedom is ehm offence of against God .
</s>
<s id="1309:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.00.51&end=00.00.53">
These are concrete words .
</s>
<s id="1309:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.09">
Ehm well , I asked ehm for a commission to be sent to look to ehm look at the situation of our Coptic brothers in Egypt , which is a moderate country ehm but has none of the fundamental rights , not even in the public ehm positions .
</s>
<s id="1309:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1309&start=00.01.10&end=00.01.14">
Europe has got to wake up , Europe has got to ehm remember its Christian roots .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1310" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="212" duration="short" durations="102.0" speed="slow" speedwm="124.7" delivery="read" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Casini Carlo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="204" duration="short" durations="99.0" speed="slow" speedwm="123.6" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN120" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1310:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.13">
Thank you President , the colleagues who have preceded me have virtually said everything .
</s>
<s id="1310:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.18">
They have mentioned the facts , they assessed them and they made specific requests .
</s>
<s id="1310:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.19&end=00.00.26">
Therefore , as I am the last on the list , I would simply like to add something which has not already been said .
</s>
<s id="1310:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.38">
My mind goes back to a very great European , ehm John Paul II , who very effectively contributed ehm to the collapse of the Berlin Wall .
</s>
<s id="1310:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.39&end=00.00.51">
And in his spiritual ehm testament said that the values that are the basis of the future civilisation , the civilisation of love , are life , peace and f- religious freedom .
</s>
<s id="1310:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.00.52&end=00.01.08">
I also ehm think of Giorgio La Pira , who is a former Mayor of Florence and who promoted many ehm conventions on ehm freedom of ehm ... religion and he said that every political conception has is based on the concept of man .
</s>
<s id="1310:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.21">
For Christian Europe , man is ehm essentially a speaking being , ehm a being capable of speaking and of ast- sustaining a dialogue with God .
</s>
<s id="1310:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.01.21&end=00.01.28">
To ehm deny man's dialogue is not only a denial of religion , but the very negation of man himself .
</s>
<s id="1310:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1310&start=00.01.28&end=00.01.48">
I trust in the Assembly and the High Representative and hand over this thoughts as a contribution to a concrete commitment on the part of our European Union , that roots are based in crit- Christianity so that will not fail to proclaim its desire to defend and promote the rights o- of human rights .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1311" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="137" duration="short" durations="64.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.4" delivery="impromptu" topic="Society and Culture" topicspec="Situation of Christians in the context of freedom of religion" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Allam Magdi Cristiano" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="long" lengthw="77" duration="short" durations="64.0" speed="slow" speedwm="72.2" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN06" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1311:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1311&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.42">
Thank you so much , well I 'll just ehm restrict my comment to a request for ehm lady Ashton , I 'd like to ask you to put on the agenda in ehm your ehm relations with Egypt , I 'd like you to put a specific request : we call upon the Egyptian authorities to to remove from the official documents and from the ID card , from passports or for any other kind of document which is requested to work in Egypt , one should remove the faith issue .
</s>
<s id="1311:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1311&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.51">
Christians are discriminated against in Egypt as soon as they show their document , because on their ID it says ' Christian ' .
</s>
<s id="1311:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1311&start=00.00.51&end=00.01.01">
Islamic terrorism is being legitimised within a context in which the discrimination against Christians is institutionalised .
</s>
<s id="1311:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1311&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.13">
This is a specific request which should be carried out and I think this would make life a lot easier for Christians , because they would not have to fight this type of discrimination .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1312" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="249" duration="short" durations="116.0" speed="slow" speedwm="128.8" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Security situation in the Sahel region" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Gualtieri Roberto" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="214" duration="short" durations="114.0" speed="slow" speedwm="112.6" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN120" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1312:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.29">
Thank you President , ehm madam High Representative ... there seems to be ehm certain agreement ehm between what has been expressed ehm by ... and an analysis of the situation , the fact that ehm the situation in the Sahel is dramatic .
</s>
<s id="1312:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.41">
We 're talking about one of the poorest countries in the world , bordering on some of these countries who , in the last few weeks , have been e- experiencing a c- a very dangerous degree of st- of instability .
</s>
<s id="1312:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.55">
An area where we have ehm terrorist infiltration , drug trafficking , which make the situation unsustainable and represent a very serious threat ehm for Europe .
</s>
<s id="1312:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.06">
Ehm Europe therefore needs to ehm take a leap ehm forward considering the development ehm of Sahel up to 2009 it appears to have been insufficient .
</s>
<s id="1312:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.17">
We therefore need a new strategy ehm for the safety of Sahel ehm which the Ministers of ehm Foreign Affairs have asked us to adopt and that we 're ex- ehm waiting for .
</s>
<s id="1312:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.01.17&end=00.01.50">
And then , these are important points and there are important points that have been made : first of all , a regional approach , and secondly , an integrated approach which will make it possible ehm for us to use in a coordinated and concrete manner the various instruments that the European Union has at its disposal , ehm realising ehm that a possible mission ehm has to be assessed very carefully , because such missions are only one of the instruments that we have at our disposal , but they can not replace political strategy .
</s>
<s id="1312:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.01.50&end=00.02.02">
Ehm therefore , our group ehm supports a renewed commitment on the part of Europe in the Sahel and we are anxious to discuss the new ehm strategy , to ehm support its implementation in detail .
</s>
<s id="1312:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1312&start=00.02.02&end=00.02.02">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1313" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="218" duration="short" durations="98.0" speed="medium" speedwm="133.5" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="Security situation in the Sahel region" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Panzeri Pier Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="207" duration="short" durations="96.0" speed="slow" speedwm="129.4" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN117" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="1313:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.27">
Thank you President ... there has ehm the request for a debate on this topic has been made frequently and frequently one has entered into commitments to the fact that nec- ehm that necessary initiatives be taken for the Sahel , to stabilise the region and to ensure a greater level of safety .
</s>
<s id="1313:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.39">
As we know , in view of the lack of borders and very vast nature of the Sahel , it 's an ideal area of transit for drug drug traffickers and for terrorist acts of Al-Qaeda .
</s>
<s id="1313:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.00.40&end=00.00.53">
The ehm weakness and fragile nature of the States in this area constitute the main problem and the threats affect the populations in the area , particularly Mauritania , ehm Mali and Niger .
</s>
<s id="1313:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.00.54&end=00.01.14">
The main topic that the European Union has before it is to prepare a credible strategy for security , which will be based on the various possible actions : ehm a e- e- development ehm strategy to coordinate the trafficking and ehm policies for security .
</s>
<s id="1313:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.01.15&end=00.01.26">
The European Union and therefore must intervene as quickly as possible and we expect a strategy from the Commission , as you said , and a strong action in the field .
</s>
<s id="1313:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.01.27&end=00.01.38">
In conclusion , my vision is clear : we need to pay greater attention to what is happening at the south of Europe , because many things are going to change and we should not be taken unawares .
</s>
<s id="1313:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.01.39&end=00.01.44">
A more far-sighted vision ehm can only work in the benefit of to the benefit of the European Union .
</s>
<s id="1313:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1313&start=00.01.44&end=00.01.45">
Thank you .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1314" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="307" duration="medium" durations="145.0" speed="slow" speedwm="127.0" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="EU Libya Framework Agreement" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Panzeri Pier Antonio" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="317" duration="medium" durations="144.0" speed="medium" speedwm="132.1" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN16" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1314:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.21">
Thank you President , I think that the work carried out by Ana Gomes is a very ehm significant contribution to what the Commission have to do in defining what the framework agreement actually will be .
</s>
<s id="1314:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.30">
Libya plays a significant role when it comes to peace , ehm security in Africa , fighting ehm illegal immigration over the Mediterranean and for energy .
</s>
<s id="1314:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.50">
Therefore , our goal for our strategy has be got to be to consolidate accession of Libya into an economic international system based on common rules and values and to do that , we 've got to have a whole series of conditions , sine qua nons and it 's not enough just to recommend .
</s>
<s id="1314:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.00.50&end=00.00.54">
When it comes to immigration , Libya obviously is a transit country .
</s>
<s id="1314:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.06">
Is it 's a very important topic , but it ca n't be just seen from the point of view of security , ehm just refoulement , ehm r- r- readmission .
</s>
<s id="1314:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.19">
We 've got to look at the economic and ehm policy issues behind migration , ehm political refugees as well and ratification of Geneva Convention , that 's important as a general backdrop to all this .
</s>
<s id="1314:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.01.20&end=00.01.25">
And we 've got to have guar- security guarantees ehm for ehm migrants themselves .
</s>
<s id="1314:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.01.27&end=00.01.43">
Economic and democratic ehm values for this country should mean that we all- get this country to widen the democratic space , the democratic values in the same country and bear in mind what 's happened in Tunisia and also bilateral agreements .
</s>
<s id="1314:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.01.44&end=00.01.52">
These bilateral agreements obviously can give a valid contribution to how we define and how we resolve problems , but they are not be-all and end-all .
</s>
<s id="1314:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.01.53&end=00.02.04">
For example , the problem that have Italian ehm fishing vessels ehm means ehm that some of these problems have not yet been resolved and it shows how much they 've not been resolved .
</s>
<s id="1314:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.02.04&end=00.02.11">
And also neighbourhood and partnership agreements should give a new framework for Libya .
</s>
<s id="1314:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.02.11&end=00.02.13">
We 've got to bring in the Parliament to this process .
</s>
<s id="1314:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.02.13&end=00.02.21">
We 've asked several times that we 're recognised or get to know , rather what the Council limit is on negotiating a f- a framework .
</s>
<s id="1314:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1314&start=00.02.22&end=00.02.30">
And , since we knew so late , ehm Commissioner , we 've got to change on that and Parliament 's got to be informed and involved on the south-Mediterranean issue .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="1315" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="145" duration="short" durations="77.0" speed="slow" speedwm="113.0" delivery="read" topic="Politics" topicspec="EU Libya Framework Agreement" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Provera Fiorello" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="166" duration="short" durations="75.0" speed="medium" speedwm="132.8" delivery="read">
<interpreter id="EN17" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="1315:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1315&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.27">
Thank you President , I 'm in favour of concluding a framework agreement w- between EU and Libya because that would be progress vis-√†-vis the past on important points - migration , economic and health cooperation and fighting AIDS ehm in particular , and also energy programmes ehm partially .
</s>
<s id="1315:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1315&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.38">
Also ehm Libya does monitor terrorist activity , inside and outside its country , in particular southern country .
</s>
<s id="1315:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1315&start=00.00.40&end=00.01.06">
Ehm p- progress has been made between the Council and the government , on ehm general things such as the Rome Statute and Status Refugees has been done , that 's progress , but a lot remains to be done quite obviously and obviously Parliament would support the agreement already negotiated would n't question that ... 'cause otherwise we 'd ehm run the risk of ehm losing accrued successes .
</s>
<s id="1315:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=1315&start=00.01.07&end=00.01.25">
And I hope that the Friendship Agreement between Italy and Libya ehm could be looked at ehm particularly that 's addressing ehm the ehm fractious issue of the colonial past and maybe we should look at political ehm specific points , that we could address to the Libyans .
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2356" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="181" duration="short" durations="101.0" speed="slow" speedwm="107.5" delivery="impromptu" topic="Environment" topicspec="Emission performance standards for new light commercial vehicles" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Gardini Elisabetta" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="156" duration="short" durations="101.0" speed="slow" speedwm="92.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN04" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="2356:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.02">
Thank you very much.
</s>
<s id="2356:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.02&end=00.00.04">
I'd like to say ...
</s>
<s id="2356:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.04&end=00.00.07">
that the result achieved is extremely ambitious.
</s>
<s id="2356:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.07&end=00.00.21">
I'd like to remind you at the moment CO2 ehm emissions reductions, sorry  CO2 emissions of about 200 grams.
</s>
<s id="2356:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.31">
So coming down from 200, 247 that's a a big cut, and I don't, I ...
</s>
<s id="2356:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.35">
and the marginal reductions are the most expensive ones, so let's be careful here.
</s>
<s id="2356:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.35&end=00.00.43">
I don't think that you can compare what we have do- done, as we have done often in this House, w- this particular /caregory/ category of vehicles with passenger cars.
</s>
<s id="2356:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.43&end=00.00.55">
These commer-, the the production and design cycles are much long-longer for commercial vehicles and w- and we only get a 1.5 percent impact of CO2 emissions for the whole sector.
</s>
<s id="2356:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.00.55&end=00.01.04">
If we haven't achieved the goals at this stage, w- we m- might nonetheless have actually been hur- hurting a sector which has already been reduced by 30 percent in size.
</s>
<s id="2356:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.01.04&end=00.01.24">
And we will be hurting above all the SMEs, that just 20, 12 hours ago in this House we were all saying we want to support SMEs because of the huge economic and social role they play: they are the real engine of growth and change and innovation in Europe.
</s>
<s id="2356:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.01.24&end=00.01.38">
So, congratulations on the work, but let's monitor the effect of this on SMEs.
</s>
<s id="2356:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2356&start=00.01.38&end=00.01.41">
Thank you.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2360" date="2011-02-14" length="short" lengthw="136" duration="short" durations="95.0" speed="slow" speedwm="85.9" delivery="impromptu" topic="Health" topicspec="One minute speeches" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="De Magistris Luigi" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="124" duration="short" durations="95.0" speed="slow" speedwm="78.3" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN18" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2360:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.03">
Thank you President.
</s>
<s id="2360:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.03&end=00.00.13">
Today, the 14th of February, is European Day of epilepsy.
</s>
<s id="2360:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.25">
That's a disease that 6 million European citizens suffer from, including 300,000 or so Italians.
</s>
<s id="2360:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.25&end=00.00.36">
And so today a large number of events have been organised by organisations, including the Italian Epilepsy Association, to increase people's awareness of this serious problem on which there's still a lack of clear information.
</s>
<s id="2360:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.36&end=00.00.40">
People are very unfamiliar with a lot of the the delicate elements of epilepsy.
</s>
<s id="2360:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.40&end=00.00.48">
A lot of progress has been made in in Europe in recent years, particularly in the 2009 directive, but there's still a lot more to be done.
</s>
<s id="2360:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.00.48&end=00.01.08">
That applies in particular to en-  ensuring that epileptics can enjoy their full rights as citizens: at the workplace, in terms of their mobility, getting access to to drugs, ehm being able to ehm follow a full school programme.
</s>
<s id="2360:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.01.08&end=00.01.25">
And so I think it's very important to take this day to think about these very important issues.
</s>
<s id="2360:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2360&start=00.01.25&end=00.01.35">
Thank you.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2364" date="2011-02-02" length="short" lengthw="247" duration="medium" durations="132.0" speed="slow" speedwm="112.3" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Situation in the Mediterranean in particula in Tunisia and Egypt" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mauro Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="204" duration="medium" durations="132.0" speed="slow" speedwm="92.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2364:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.11">
Thank you, President.
</s>
<s id="2364:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.28">
Lady Ashton, I've never been particularly ehm kind to you, but I'm bound to admit that history is doing everything it can to make your life more difficult, ehm so I do hope that what I say now will help you.
</s>
<s id="2364:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.41">
The first thing I want to say, and I want to say it very clearly, is that States are guarantors of the rights of their citizens, they are not owners of the lives of their citizens.
</s>
<s id="2364:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.41&end=00.00.49">
And when ehm the governments act as if they were ehm in charge of the lives of their citizens, then they become regimes instead of governments.
</s>
<s id="2364:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.49&end=00.00.59">
That's what's happening or had been happening in Egypt, ehm since for many years now we've seen regimes in Egypt since eight ...
</s>
<s id="2364:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.00">
one ...
</s>
<s id="2364:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.00&end=00.01.01">
ehm independence.
</s>
<s id="2364:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.06">
And ehm we should be on the side of those who are ehm in the streets of Egypt at the moment.
</s>
<s id="2364:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.11">
The next question is for us on the European Union.
</s>
<s id="2364:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.11&end=00.01.22">
We need to have a strategy for the Mediterranean basin, and that means we have to evaluate the failure of the Barcelona process.
</s>
<s id="2364:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.22&end=00.01.31">
Ehm these are political activities, they are political games they don't serve any useful purpose, they have not achieved anything at all.
</s>
<s id="2364:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.31&end=00.01.42">
And therefore we must put an end to them and we must start with a real strategy.
</s>
<s id="2364:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.01.42&end=00.02.02">
We got to think it through and implement it as we have done in the interest of Eastern Europe and as we did ehm in the interest of the Balkans, although we had to be pushed.
</s>
<s id="2364:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.02.02&end=00.02.11">
So that strategy will ehm w- ehm work with a single voice for that region, we won't be saying anything.
</s>
<s id="2364:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2364&start=00.02.11&end=00.02.12">
Thank you.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2368" date="2011-01-19" length="short" lengthw="252" duration="medium" durations="134.0" speed="slow" speedwm="112.8" delivery="impromptu" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Cost of examining asylum seekers‚Äô applications in Member States" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Pallone Alfredo" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="198" duration="medium" durations="134.0" speed="slow" speedwm="88.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2368:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.34">
Thank you ehm President, but I wouldn't like to sound a dissonant note here because I really am convinced that the ehm even in semantic terms the the the the what we were hearing from the various groups is that the is about the relationship between the savings to be made and the question of the asylum right is something that has negative connotations.
</s>
<s id="2368:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.37">
I'll try to explain very briefly what I mean.
</s>
<s id="2368:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.37&end=00.00.39">
I really do believe ...
</s>
<s id="2368:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.39&end=00.00.45">
that ehm the real problem here is harmonisation, it's not a problem of cost.
</s>
<s id="2368:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.45&end=00.00.50">
It's not ehm it's not an ideological problem, it is a cultural one.
</s>
<s id="2368:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.50&end=00.00.54">
Unfortunately, for cultural reasons ...
</s>
<s id="2368:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.54&end=00.00.59">
not ideological reasons, we have different approaches to this problem and we have to do something about that.
</s>
<s id="2368:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.03">
The countries that are most exposed to this problem are those of the South.
</s>
<s id="2368:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.13">
They have a much greater sense of hospitality than other parts of the European Union because they have  much closer ehm connection with this problem.
</s>
<s id="2368:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.19">
So the problem in Italy has ehm got a lot worse and the prices, and the costs are going up.
</s>
<s id="2368:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.21">
We're talking about 30 billion euros.
</s>
<s id="2368:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.21&end=00.01.22">
We are trying to reduce that cost.
</s>
<s id="2368:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.22&end=00.01.24">
We don't really believe in that.
</s>
<s id="2368:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.24&end=00.01.29">
Ehm you know, ehm how can we cut 20 percent of this.
</s>
<s id="2368:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.39">
There's a problem of disability which is ehm often these political refugees have disabilities as well because they have been tortured.
</s>
<s id="2368:16" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.39&end=00.01.52">
And we have to talk about the protection and that's another ehm question of course, it's not just a question of who we allow in, ehm we ehm have to ...
</s>
<s id="2368:17" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.01.52&end=00.02.05">
say that this is a Europe of freedom, a Europe where we protect rights ...
</s>
<s id="2368:18" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2368&start=00.02.05&end=00.02.14">
[The President cuts off the speaker]
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2372" date="2011-02-02" length="short" lengthw="196" duration="short" durations="110.0" speed="slow" speedwm="106.9" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Referendum on the future status of Southern Sudan" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Milana Guido" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="SD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="186" duration="short" durations="110.0" speed="slow" speedwm="101.5" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2372:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.01">
Thank you.
</s>
<s id="2372:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.01&end=00.00.05">
I don't want to spoil ehm the mood.
</s>
<s id="2372:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.05&end=00.00.09">
Ehm everyone's so pleased.
</s>
<s id="2372:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.09&end=00.00.21">
It's true  we have just been through a phase that started in 2005, when diplomacy ehm did its work is in the best possible way.
</s>
<s id="2372:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.23">
There's still a lot to be done.
</s>
<s id="2372:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.23&end=00.00.29">
This is a young country, will be a young country ehm when secession is completed.
</s>
<s id="2372:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.29&end=00.00.47">
And it's a country that still has to determine its borders, ehm and the #### of Abyei subject to conflict, ehm but the most important thing is of course ehm to integrate the country into the international ehm system.
</s>
<s id="2372:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.49">
So there's a few things that need to be done.
</s>
<s id="2372:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.00.49&end=00.01.09">
We now t- we need to determine a strategy for South Sudan, we have to do so in ehm not waiting for 9th of July, we got to start right away ehm start on February 7th when the results of the election are officially published.
</s>
<s id="2372:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.22">
And immediately, right away we must open up our international service to this country, send a delegation to South Sudan right away.
</s>
<s id="2372:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.01.22&end=00.01.30">
That's the only way to help out with a process like this.
</s>
<s id="2372:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.01.30&end=00.01.34">
That's intelligent diplomacy, with a strategy.
</s>
<s id="2372:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2372&start=00.01.34&end=00.01.50">
That's the only way to help this country in the road to demacr- democracy and the first thing they have to do is to write their constitution, and there Europe can really help them a lot.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2376" date="2011-02-02" length="medium" lengthw="703" duration="medium" durations="314.0" speed="medium" speedwm="134.3" delivery="impromptu" topic="Economics and Finance" topicspec="Agreements on trade in bananas" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Balzani Francesca" gender="F" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="S&D">
<st language="it" length="medium" lengthw="504" duration="medium" durations="314.0" speed="slow" speedwm="96.3" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="NA" gender="NA" native="NA">
<s id="2376:1">
Thank you Madam President, dear colleagues.
</s>
<s id="2376:2">
It seems to me that this have been a very interesting debate ..
</s>
<s id="2376:3">
and it did allow us to express fears and concerns that we'd already dealt with on the Committee.
</s>
<s id="2376:4">
And I would like to underscore once again a very important fact which I think we lose sight of sometimes.
</s>
<s id="2376:5">
These agreements are up- the updating of a commitment entered into by the European Union as a member of the World Trade Organisation.
</s>
<s id="2376:6">
Let's not forget ehm this.
</s>
<s id="2376:7">
So these are agreements through which the European Union ehm is able to finally commit itself to resolving a very serious problem with important countries, ehm the the the European Union was actually breaching a principle of non-discrimination.
</s>
<s id="2376:8">
And so these are agreements which actually restore EU credibility.
</s>
<s id="2376:9">
We are now a credible and responsible member of the World Trade Organisation again.
</s>
<s id="2376:10">
So it's an agreement ehm and obviously it's the end of a whole pr- process of negotiation and there was a lot of there were lot of dis- disputes, there were controversies ac- actually contaminating ehm negotiations on other agreements but is a it is like all definitive agreements aiming at striking a new balance.
</s>
<s id="2376:11">
And this agreement does strike a new balance.
</s>
<s id="2376:12">
We've written that in the resolution and it it tries to strike a balance ehm in order to help th- the vulnerable developing countries.
</s>
<s id="2376:13">
These banana accompanying measures ehm will obviously now be closely monitored.
</s>
<s id="2376:14">
And I think that's one of the most important points.
</s>
<s id="2376:15">
Obviously we have we have planned.
</s>
<s id="2376:16">
This is important we have planned these accompanying measures.
</s>
<s id="2376:17">
It is even more important to have this assessment of the impact of the functioning of these accompanying measures.
</s>
<s id="2376:18">
And we have to ehm c- commit to this and we are pleased that both Council and the Commission have ehm entered into a commitment.
</s>
<s id="2376:19">
They won't ehm they won't ehm fail to keep an eye on the situation and they've also expressed their willingness to act and to propose different measures were they to be necessary.
</s>
<s id="2376:20">
And the POSEI itself ehm was put into the motion resolution.
</s>
<s id="2376:21">
This is also a delicate point that we have to keep an eye on.
</s>
<s id="2376:22">
Ehm because obviously we obviously we have to look forward ehm to the use of the PO- POSEI and we have to adapt POSEI's ehm financial envelopes that can meet the needs of ehm th the out- outermost countries, an- and meet the needs of European gr- growers and the growers at the outermost regions.
</s>
<s id="2376:23">
So their needs will be kept a close eye on as well.
</s>
<s id="2376:24">
And there's something else I'm very happy about, that is the the there's recognition of the need to keep an eye on the transparency of the food supply chain.
</s>
<s id="2376:25">
We always talk about the growers but there's also this big issue of distribution of bananas within the European market.
</s>
<s id="2376:26">
So there's lots to be done in the future, we have to monitor the effects of the agreement, we have to look at how the banana accompanying measures work, we have to look at the suitability of the POSEI to keep an eye and help the European growers and the outermost growers.
</s>
<s id="2376:27">
But also we have to keep an eye on the food supply chain ### to broaden ehm activities to look at the entire food distribution chain which has an impact on the final cost of the fruit.
</s>
<s id="2376:28">
We also have to look after consumer interests.
</s>
<s id="2376:29">
That's something should be close to our hearts, as close to our hearts as as as many of the other concerns expressed in this resolution.
</s>
<s id="2376:30">
But ehm all these things ehm and not last con- concerns for the consumers have to takes take their beginning in in assessment of the present situation.
</s>
<s id="2376:31">
The present situation involved overcoming ehm these disputes.
</s>
<s id="2376:32">
We lost this dispute with the US and with Latin American countries, and so we we have to have these agreements, we have to give our concern because they're actually necessary point of departures so that we can now get these new measures going, make them work, these banana accompanying measures.
</s>
<s id="2376:33">
I hope this will allow us to ehm look after other concerns as well, the concerns of consumers, as consumers are concerned about the transparency of the food supply chain.
</s>
<s id="2376:34">
I hope th- this wil- this agreement will allow us to improve the functioning of the European common market in bananas, help protect the interests of European banana growers and w- at the same time these agreements have allowed us to ehm put an end to disputed in the World Trade Organization which the EU belongs to.
</s>
<s id="2376:35">
Thank you very much.
</s>
<s id="2376:36">
None
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2380" date="2011-02-03" length="short" lengthw="141" duration="short" durations="88.0" speed="slow" speedwm="96.1" delivery="impromptu" topic="Environment" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="De Magistris Luigi" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="126" duration="short" durations="88.0" speed="slow" speedwm="85.9" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN18" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2380:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.05">
Thank you President.
</s>
<s id="2380:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.05&end=00.00.14">
The resolution adopted by the majority today, on the waste emergency in Campania, sends out a very significant signal.
</s>
<s id="2380:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.14&end=00.00.21">
The Campania emergency has become a European emergency, and this is a decision in favour of the citizens of Campania.
</s>
<s id="2380:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.30">
We are saying ‚Äòno' to funds being used mainly to consolidate corrupt policies ...
</s>
<s id="2380:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.30&end=00.00.34">
for the benefit of unscrupulous businessmen and the camorra.
</s>
<s id="2380:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.34&end=00.00.48">
We are saying ‚Äòyes' to a a credible waste treatment plan which should be compatible with environmental concerns, rather than having uncontrolled landfill sites in national natural parks and ehm incinerators generating dioxin.
</s>
<s id="2380:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.48&end=00.00.50">
We need waste management compatible with the environment.
</s>
<s id="2380:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.50&end=00.00.59">
We're also saying that we are against ehm local auth- authorities being ehm criminalised.
</s>
<s id="2380:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2380&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.28">
So there's an important message here for the Berlusconi Government and the regional government led by Caldoro, up until now all they've done is is come up with a few ### bites and they've worked for the benefit of the local mafia organisations.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2384" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="131" duration="short" durations="100.0" speed="slow" speedwm="78.6" delivery="impromptu" topic="Transport" topicspec="Explanations of vote" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Uggias Giommaria" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="144" duration="short" durations="100.0" speed="slow" speedwm="86.4" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN76" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2384:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.08">
Thank you Madam President.
</s>
<s id="2384:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.08&end=00.00.20">
I'd like to congratulate Mr Cancian on the excellent job that he's done in bringing this ehm text ehm to a conclusion.
</s>
<s id="2384:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.20&end=00.00.26">
But Mr Mastella will allow me to disagree with him ehm when he says that this is a major achievement.
</s>
<s id="2384:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.26&end=00.00.38">
Citizens are still only protected when they go more than 250 kilometers in bus or coach.
</s>
<s id="2384:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.44">
But and where are the new where are the rights protected in that?
</s>
<s id="2384:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.44&end=00.00.54">
As Mrs Meissner said, there are whole states - Cyprus, Luxembourg and Malta - which are excluded from this.
</s>
<s id="2384:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.54&end=00.00.58">
That's why our vote was abstention.
</s>
<s id="2384:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.09">
We didn't vote against because there are some good rights protected here; for example those of the handicapped or people of reduced mobility.
</s>
<s id="2384:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.01.09&end=00.01.13">
That's why we abstained.
</s>
<s id="2384:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2384&start=00.01.13&end=00.01.40">
But we think that we need to return to this subject as soon as possible in order to protect citizens' rights in a better way.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2388" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="266" duration="medium" durations="129.0" speed="slow" speedwm="123.7" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Immediate EU measures in support of Italy and other Member States affected by exceptional migration flows" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mauro Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="195" duration="medium" durations="129.0" speed="slow" speedwm="90.7" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN04" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="2388:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.02">
Thank you President.
</s>
<s id="2388:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.02&end=00.00.22">
Commissioner, above all I'd like to thank you for your commitment that you're showing here and I think that you'll be showing even more commitment in the near future in order to deal with this humanitarian emergency.
</s>
<s id="2388:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.27">
But you know full well, as I do, that the real emergency is not the humanitarian one.
</s>
<s id="2388:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.27&end=00.00.31">
The humanitarian crisis is just the effect, the consequence.
</s>
<s id="2388:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.51">
The real emergency is the fact ehm that in these huge uprisings which are affecting the entire Arab Maghreb area Europe seems ina- inadequate, unable of coming up with a new strategy for Mediterranean, we've tried to get a Mediterranean policy, we've never succeeded.
</s>
<s id="2388:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.51&end=00.00.53">
The Lisbon ehm fr- Process has failed.
</s>
<s id="2388:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.53&end=00.00.56">
The European Union on the Mediterranean has failed.
</s>
<s id="2388:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.00.56&end=00.01.01">
We don't have a an appropriate vision of the real problems here, that are on the table.
</s>
<s id="2388:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.01.01&end=00.01.06">
We need to deal with the whole thing and and  we don't have the Council here today.
</s>
<s id="2388:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.19">
We asked the Council to actually look at this whole issue o- of coming up with a European strategy not just for the problem of illegal migration and immigration, but the whole problem of democracy and freedom in the whole Mediterranean area.
</s>
<s id="2388:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.27">
When the Sov- when the ehm when the iron curtain came down we all worked together, shoulder to shoulder and we've found practical answers to problems.
</s>
<s id="2388:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.01.27&end=00.01.44">
And now that we've got w- w- of course we had the problem of th- th- the thousands of Polish people coming here and but we dealt with the problem of integration ehm of the whole of Eastern Europe.
</s>
<s id="2388:13" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.01.44&end=00.02.00">
But now when it comes to the Mediterranean, we're just keeping quiet, we're keeping mum, but we need a strategy, without a vision, a strategy we won't be able to come up with answers.
</s>
<s id="2388:14" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.02.00&end=00.02.08">
So w- we appreciate your efforts here, your good efforts here, and we leave it at that.
</s>
<s id="2388:15" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2388&start=00.02.08&end=00.02.09">
Thank you.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2392" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="197" duration="short" durations="118.0" speed="slow" speedwm="100.2" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Immediate EU measures in support of Italy and other Member States affected by exceptional migration flows" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Borghezio Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="EFD">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="176" duration="short" durations="118.0" speed="slow" speedwm="89.5" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN04" gender="F" native="Y">
<s id="2392:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.21">
I'd like to thank the Commissioner for h- her promises, although the European Union with with with all these subsidies given ehm throughout the world, the money it's given to its European delegations throughout the world, it could have been aware of what was happening quicker.
</s>
<s id="2392:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.22">
It didn't.
</s>
<s id="2392:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.38">
The opinion didn't realise what was happening and ehm the the social international well the socialist international, the Tunisian dictator belonged to that, and it is a fantastic management, social management of that country's given rise to disasters, although he was a member of the Socialist International.
</s>
<s id="2392:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.00.38&end=00.00.48">
We'd like to know from the Commissioner why he doesn't talk clearly about distribution of of these migrants between the various member states, the sharing out.
</s>
<s id="2392:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.00.48&end=00.01.03">
Is it's not right an- an- and the ehm it's not right that this problem is just a burden of those who have ehm maritime borders ehm who are geographically close to the countries of Northern Africa.
</s>
<s id="2392:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.03&end=00.01.06">
This is a crucial point.
</s>
<s id="2392:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.06&end=00.01.10">
W- ehm Frontex also has very sc- scarce resources.
</s>
<s id="2392:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.10&end=00.01.14">
Ehm Frontex sent along two experts ehm one on Lampedusa.
</s>
<s id="2392:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.14&end=00.01.29">
There's a real humanitarian tragedy going on, an- and we need a task force th- that an approp- appropriate task force.
</s>
<s id="2392:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.29&end=00.01.39">
Let's make up for the mistakes of the recent past.
</s>
<s id="2392:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.39&end=00.01.46">
This is a very ser- serious situation which can get even worse.
</s>
<s id="2392:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2392&start=00.01.46&end=00.01.58">
Th- there can be health problems, ehm Lampedusa really is running out of water, already.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2396" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="144" duration="short" durations="98.0" speed="slow" speedwm="88.2" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Immediate EU measures in support of Italy and other Member States affected by exceptional migration flows" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Crocetta Rosario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="S&D">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="148" duration="short" durations="98.0" speed="slow" speedwm="90.6" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN36" gender="M" native="NA">
<s id="2396:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.06">
Thank you President.
</s>
<s id="2396:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.16">
I'd like to thank ehm the Commissioner for looking at Tunisia seriously.
</s>
<s id="2396:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.16&end=00.00.22">
Now, in this debate I have to say I would have liked to call call it a different term.
</s>
<s id="2396:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.22&end=00.00.28">
All about supporting Tunisia and countries fighting dictatorships and fighting for human rights.
</s>
<s id="2396:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.42">
But in the end a humanitarian emergency is made of the fact that one of the greatest world powers, Italy, has issues in terms of how to deal with 5,000 people arriving in Lam- Lampedusa.
</s>
<s id="2396:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.42&end=00.00.53">
It's a problem, granted, but we've got people coming into Sicily every day and there's even an airport where people can be transported to.
</s>
<s id="2396:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.00.53&end=00.01.05">
So we need to be clear here: we're not discussing Frontex or how we stop these boats landing.
</s>
<s id="2396:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.07">
Ultimately we try to help people.
</s>
<s id="2396:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.01.07&end=00.01.19">
We argue that these people should stand up for democracy, so we need to make sure that we have the capacity to welcome them, and extending visas.
</s>
<s id="2396:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2396&start=00.01.19&end=00.01.38">
That's something that Italy can do to really try and help these countries.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2400" date="2011-02-15" length="short" lengthw="151" duration="short" durations="105.0" speed="slow" speedwm="86.3" delivery="impromptu" topic="Justice" topicspec="Eavesdropping scandal in Bulgaria" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Rinaldi Niccol√≤" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="ALDE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="140" duration="short" durations="105.0" speed="slow" speedwm="80.0" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN36" gender="M" native="NA">
<s id="2400:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.06">
Thank you President.
</s>
<s id="2400:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.06&end=00.00.13">
I'm a liberal democrat both in Europe and in Italy.
</s>
<s id="2400:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.13&end=00.00.28">
Sometimes, in my, in my country, with my party counterparts we're often dubbed communists just because we're in opposition to the current government.
</s>
<s id="2400:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.37">
And from what we've read it seems that the same is happening to my liberal democrats or socialists in Bulgaria.
</s>
<s id="2400:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.37&end=00.00.43">
They are being called criminals simply because they are in the opposition in Bulgaria.
</s>
<s id="2400:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.43&end=00.00.47">
Now this is a ehm a shift that we don't really like.
</s>
<s id="2400:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.47&end=00.00.58">
Now sometimes you can jest about these things ehm but this sort of conduct can actually become very dangerous.
</s>
<s id="2400:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.00.58&end=00.01.17">
I have to say that my Foreign Affairs Minister just yesterday given all that's happening in Tunisia and Egypt went to Damascus in Syria and said that Syria is a democratic country that fully satisfies the requirements for modernisation that citizens are calling for.
</s>
<s id="2400:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2400&start=00.01.17&end=00.01.45">
If that's what our representatives are saying, we, in the European Parliament, need to speak out, but you, in the Commission, also need to keep a very close eye on this.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2404" date="2011-02-16" length="short" lengthw="294" duration="medium" durations="149.0" speed="slow" speedwm="118.4" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Media law in Hungary" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Scurria Marco" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="216" duration="medium" durations="149.0" speed="slow" speedwm="87.0" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2404:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.02">
Thank you ehm President.
</s>
<s id="2404:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.02&end=00.00.21">
Ehm I'm speaking, in this debate, but with a little embarrassment, I have to say, because the ehm Commissioner has pretty well told us that there's no point having the debate.
</s>
<s id="2404:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.21&end=00.00.24">
Ehm there is no contest here.
</s>
<s id="2404:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.24&end=00.00.31">
In all probability, if he had listened to our other colleagues, we'd already have said.
</s>
<s id="2404:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.31&end=00.00.51">
And what they said in previous occasions, in the committee meetings and here in ehm plenary, well, maybe it would have been better to wait for a little while, because the Hungarian Government has continued to show willing ehm to go some way to meet ehm the comments addressed to it by the [video freezes].
</s>
<s id="2404:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.51&end=00.00.59">
Which of course is ehm awkward ehm given that the country is holding the Presidency ehm of the EU at the moment.
</s>
<s id="2404:7" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.00.59&end=00.01.05">
It would be very embarrassing for them not to follow the ehm instructions of the Commission.
</s>
<s id="2404:8" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.01.05&end=00.01.14">
But we do have to go forward, and I'm sure that there are more than one ideological factor and political factor involved here.
</s>
<s id="2404:9" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.01.14&end=00.01.23">
So for those reasons we need the debate and that's why the resolutions have been put forward that we'll be voting on tomorrow.
</s>
<s id="2404:10" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.01.23&end=00.01.56">
Ehm Perhaps we should have a little more ehm faith ehm in governments that have been elected democratically by their people, including the Hungarian Government, elected with a very big majority, by the way, by their people ehm I don't think there was any need for them to manipulate the government to obtain a broad-base support in their own country.
</s>
<s id="2404:11" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.01.56&end=00.02.26">
So I think that the most useful thing we can do would be to ehm call upon our socialist and liberal ehm colleagues, who have submitted ehm their ehm motion for resolution to ehm withdraw it ehm not to ehm make fools of themselves and to leave this Parliament ehm to deal with real issues ehm that are needed there by the citizens of Europe.
</s>
<s id="2404:12" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2404&start=00.02.26&end=00.02.29">
Thank you and thank you to our Commissioner for her work.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="2408" date="2011-02-16" length="short" lengthw="158" duration="short" durations="85.0" speed="slow" speedwm="111.5" delivery="impromptu" topic="Politics" topicspec="Media law in Hungary" type="English interpretations" comments="NA">
<speaker name="Mauro Mario" gender="M" country="Italy" politfunc="MEP" politgroup="PPE">
<st language="it" length="short" lengthw="124" duration="short" durations="85.0" speed="slow" speedwm="87.5" delivery="impromptu">
<interpreter id="EN13" gender="M" native="Y">
<s id="2408:1" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.00&end=00.00.05">
Thank you.
</s>
<s id="2408:2" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.05&end=00.00.11">
Ehm ...
</s>
<s id="2408:3" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.11&end=00.00.28">
Although I really would like to believe that the people who have so harshly criticised Hungary's ehm act are really just trying to talk about media freedom, I think that we do have to have some respect for the work done by the Commission and b-  other substantive points made in debate in Parliament.
</s>
<s id="2408:4" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.28&end=00.00.36">
I think too that we have to shoulder the responsibility for turning an unfortunate page in the history of this Parliament and we should decide not to vote tomorrow.
</s>
<s id="2408:5" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.36&end=00.00.52">
Simply ehm cancel a resolution based on ehm content that no longer is what's happening in the real world, as the Commissioner has told us.
</s>
<s id="2408:6" video="http://amelia.sslmit.unibo.it/video/video.php?id=2408&start=00.00.52&end=00.01.25">
So I'd like to call upon Council and Commission informally to perhaps get in touch with the Conference of Presidents, so that we can get the necessary exchange of information so that to- tomorrow in ehm Plenary we can vote before we de- vote on the resolution vote not to vote on it and put an end to this ideological debate.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>